{"title_page": "Travel restrictions related to the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic", "text_new": "{{about|international travel restrictions|domestic travel restrictions and lockdowns|National responses to the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic}}\n{{short description|Restrictions by countries intended to stop spread of disease}}\n{{Current disaster|event=pandemic|date=March 2020}}\n{{expand list|date=March 2020}}\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic sidebar|expanded=issues}}[[File:COVID-19 Outbreak World Map-GlobalTravelBan.svg|thumb|500px|Some of the countries that have imposed a global travel ban in response to the COVID-19 pandemic, as of April 5, 2020 {{legend|firebrick|Current ban on foreign travelers}}{{legend|blue|Former ban on foreign travelers}}]]\n\nAs a result of the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]], many countries and regions have imposed quarantines, entry bans, or other restrictions for citizens of or recent travelers to the most affected areas.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/article/coronavirus-travel-restrictions.html|title=Coronavirus Travel Restrictions, Across the Globe|date=26 March 2020|work=The New York Times}}</ref> Other countries and regions have imposed global restrictions that apply to all foreign countries and territories.\n\nTogether with a decreased willingness to travel, the restrictions have had a [[socio-economic impact of the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|negative economic and social impact]] on the travel sector in those regions. A possible long-term impact has been a decline of [[business travel]] and international conferencing, and the rise of their virtual, online equivalents.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.jpost.com/Opinion/The-long-term-effects-of-the-coronavirus-619118|title=The long-term effects of the coronavirus|website=The Jerusalem Post {{!}} JPost.com|access-date=2020-03-12}}</ref> Concerns have been raised over the effectiveness of travel restrictions to contain the spread of [[COVID-19]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Belluz |first1=Julia |last2=Steven |first2=Hoffman |title=The evidence on travel bans for diseases like coronavirus is clear: They don\u2019t work |url=https://www.vox.com/2020/1/23/21078325/wuhan-china-coronavirus-travel-ban |accessdate=2 April 2020 |work=Vox |date=Jan 23, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Nsikan |first1=Akpan |title=Coronavirus spikes outside China show travel bans aren\u2019t working |url=https://www.nationalgeographic.com/science/2020/02/why-travel-restrictions-are-not-stopping-coronavirus-covid-19/ |accessdate=2 April 2020 |work=National Geographic |date=24 February 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n\nThe [[European Union]] rejected the idea of suspending the [[Schengen Agreement|Schengen free travel zone]] and introducing border controls with Italy,<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.dw.com/en/coronavirus-eu-rules-out-schengen-border-closures-amid-italy-outbreak/a-52497811|title=Coronavirus: EU rules out Schengen border closures amid Italy outbreak|date=24 February 2020|publisher=Deutsche Welle}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/opinion/articles/2020-02-25/salvini-and-le-pen-don-t-have-a-european-coronavirus-cure|title=Salvini and Le Pen Don't Have a Coronavirus Cure|date=25 February 2020|work=[[Bloomberg News]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/coronavirus-europe-open-borders-eu-italy-france-britain-germany-spain-a9362536.html|title=Coronavirus: Europe's open borders threatened by spread of disease|date=28 February 2020|work=[[The Independent]]}}</ref> a decision which has been [[Criticism of response to the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|criticized]] by some European politicians.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.scmp.com/news/china/diplomacy/article/3073897/coronavirus-european-borders-likely-remain-open-despite-crisis|title=Coronavirus: European borders likely to remain open despite crisis in Italy, observers say|date=7 March 2020|work=[[South China Morning Post]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/02/26/world/europe/coronavirus-european-union.html|title=Coronavirus Nightmare Could Be the End for Europe's Borderless Dream|date=26 February 2020|work=[[The New York Times]]}}</ref> After some EU member states announced complete closure of their national borders to foreign nationals,<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/tamarathiessen/2020/03/14/coronavirus-europe-closes-borders-tourists/|title=Coronavirus: Some Of These 24 European Countries Have Closed Their Borders To Tourists|date=14 March 2020|work=[[Forbes]]}}</ref> the [[European Commission]] President [[Ursula von der Leyen]] said that \"Certain controls may be justified, but general travel bans are not seen as being the most effective by the World Health Organization.\"<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ft.com/content/4e89ec5c-6565-11ea-b3f3-fe4680ea68b5|title=Denmark, Poland and Czechs seal borders over coronavirus|date=12 March 2020|work=Financial Times}}</ref> The United States suspended travel from the [[Schengen Area]] and later the [[Common Travel Area]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.whitehouse.gov/presidential-actions/proclamation-suspension-entry-immigrants-nonimmigrants-certain-additional-persons-pose-risk-transmitting-2019-novel-coronavirus/|title=Proclamation\u2014Suspension of Entry as Immigrants and Nonimmigrants of Certain Additional Persons Who Pose a Risk of Transmitting 2019 Novel Coronavirus|publisher=White House}}</ref>\n\n==Countries and territories implementing a global travel ban ==\n=== Asia ===\n*{{flag|Azerbaijan}}: Effective March 23, 2020, passengers are not allowed to enter Azerbaijan except passengers with a work permit and passengers with a special permission issued by the government of Azerbaijan.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://restrictions.info/news/detail/3010 | title=Azerbaijan - restriction update 23.03.2020 02:06 UTC: COVID-19 Travel Restrictions Database}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Brunei}}: Effective 24 March 2020, all foreigners are not allowed to enter Brunei on all border checkpoints, including those on transit purposes.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://thescoop.co/2020/03/13/covid-19-live-updates/ |title = COVID-19 live updates: Tally climbs to 114 with 5 new infections|date = 13 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.brudirect.com/news.php?id=89853 |title=Minister Of Home Affairs Explained The Control Of Foreigner's Entry Into The Country |publisher=Brudirect.com |date= |accessdate=2020-03-30}}</ref>\n*{{flag|China}}: Effective 28 March 2020, all foreigners holding visas or residence permits still valid to the time of this announcement issued on 26 March. All specific visa regulations and entry by foreign nationals with [[APEC Business Travel Card]]s will also be suspended.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fmprc.gov.cn/mfa_eng/wjbxw/t1761867.shtml|title=Ministry of Foreign Affairs of the People's Republic of China, National Immigration Administration Announcement on the Temporary Suspension of Entry by Foreign Nationals Holding Valid Chinese Visas or Residence Permits|publisher=Ministry of Foreign Affairs of the People's Republic of China|date=2020-03-26}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Cyprus}}: The Cypriot government has announced that only its citizens, along with other Europeans working on the island and people with special permits will be allowed into the country for a 15-day period beginning on March 15.<ref>[https://www.bbc.com/news/live/world-51866403 As it happened- Coronavirus on Friday, 19:55 13 March 2020- Cyprus limits entry to country] ''/www.bbc.com'', accessed 15 March 2020</ref>\n*{{Flag|Georgia}}: The Georgian government imposed a ban on all foreign citizens entering the country and closed its borders. Georgia also halted all air travel with other countries on March 20. All restrictions end April 21.<ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://www.nytimes.com/reuters/2020/03/23/world/europe/23reuters-health-coronavirus-georgia.html|title=Georgia Bans Passenger Traffic on Domestic Railway Over Coronavirus|date=2020-03-23|work=The New York Times|access-date=2020-04-05|url-status=live|agency=Reuters|publication-place=Tbilisi|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Hong Kong}}: All non-Hong Kong residents who have been in overseas countries/territories (i.e. excluding mainland China, Macau and Taiwan) in the past 14 days are barred from entering Hong Kong, with exceptions provided for certain groups of non-Hong Kong residents such as spouses and minor children of Hong Kong residents as well as Macao residents who are registered under the Macao scheme under agreement between the Macau and the Hong Kong Government, and passengers are no longer allowed to transit through [[Hong Kong International Airport]] for two weeks starting from 25 March 2020. Non-Hong Kong residents arriving from mainland China, Macau and Taiwan who have not been in any overseas countries/territories in the past 14 days are exempted from the ban, but they are still subject to compulsory quarantine for 14 days same as all other arrivals to Hong Kong.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.info.gov.hk/gia/general/202003/24/P2020032400050.htm |title = Government announces enhancements to anti-epidemic measures in four aspects}}</ref>\n*{{flag|India}}: Effective 13 March 2020, all tourist visas and OCI entries were suspended until at least 15 April, while holders of these visas who were already in the country can stay. Also tightened/closed their border with neighboring countries.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/politics-and-nation/coronavirus-a-pandemic-india-shuts-doors-for-outsiders-under-self-imposed-quarantine/articleshow/74582547.cms|title=Coronavirus a pandemic: India shuts doors for outsiders, under self imposed quarantine|date=12 March 2020|work=The Economic Times|accessdate=12 March 2020}}</ref> On the same date, India also mandated 14-day quarantine for citizens returning from seven countries: China, France, Germany, Iran, Italy, South Korea and Spain.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/03/india-suspends-visas-attempt-coronavirus-spread-200312035057594.html|title=India suspends visas in attempt to contain coronavirus spread|work=www.aljazeera.com|accessdate=12 March 2020|publisher=AlJazeera}}</ref> Starting March 18, restrictions were extended to prohibit any flights from Western Europe and Turkey as the epidemic worsened and staying home rather than evacuating became seen as a better solution.<ref>{{cite web|accessdate=2020-03-21|title=India blocks out Europe, Turkey|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/india-news/india-blocks-out-europe-turkey/story-IIig07orTgrvnwVcIBMiHJ.html|date=17 March 2020|website=Hindustan Times}}</ref> All international flights to India were be suspended for a week starting March 22.<ref>{{cite web|accessdate=2020-03-19|title=Coronavirus: India bars international commercial passenger flights from landing in country for one week|url=https://gulfnews.com/world/asia/india/coronavirus-india-bars-international-commercial-passenger-flights-from-landing-in-country-for-one-week-1.1584620182303|website=gulfnews.com}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Israel}}: Effective 12 March 2020, foreign travelers from any country are denied entry, unless a specific permit is given by the Foreign Ministry and the person can prove the ability to remain under home isolation for 14 days. Israeli citizens and permanents residents are required to enter 14-day home isolation.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://govextra.gov.il/ministry-of-health/corona/corona-virus-en/|title=The Novel Coronavirus - Israel Ministry of Health|website=corona-virus}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Jordan}}: Effective 17 March 2020 Jordan will stop all incoming and outgoing passenger flights into the country.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/health-coronavirus-jordan-idUSL8N2B70IT|title=Jordan tightens lockdown to combat coronavirus|date=2020-03-14|work=Reuters|access-date=2020-03-15|language=en}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Macau}}: Effective 19 March 2020, all non-residents are prohibited to enter, except residents of mainland China, of Hong Kong and of Taiwan.<ref>{{cite web |title=Macao to ban overseas travellers in effort further to control COVID-19 locally |url=https://www.gov.mo/en/news/123607/ |website=Macao SAR Government Portal |accessdate=19 March 2020|date=17 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Macao to ban re-entry of any registered foreign non-resident workers, after stroke of midnight Thursday |url=https://www.gov.mo/en/news/123706/ |website=Macao SAR Government Portal |accessdate=19 March 2020 |date=18 March 2020}}</ref> On 5 April 2020, the Macanese government has announced the closure of the [[Hong Kong\u2013Zhuhai\u2013Macau Bridge]] which means all the transportation between Macao and Hong Kong has been suspended.<ref>{{cite web |title=MHong Kong-Macau delta bridge bus link suspended over COVID-19 threat (Update) |url=https://macaunews.mo/hong-kong-macau-delta-bridge-bus-link-suspended-over-covid-19-threat-update/ |website=Macao News |accessdate=5 April 2020 |date=5 April 2020}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Malaysia}}: All citizens are [[2020 Malaysia movement control order|prohibited]] from leaving the country while foreigners are prohibited from entering the country effective March 18, 2020. Airports and airspace remain open.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.straitstimes.com/asia/se-asia/malaysia-to-impose-lockdown-from-wednesday-to-march-31|title=Malaysia to impose lockdown from Wednesday to March 31|date=March 17, 2020|website=Straits Times}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Myanmar}}: Effective 30 March 2020 (23:39 - Myanmar Standard Time), all international flights except special categories of flights are not allowed to land in Myanmar until 13 April 2020 (23:59 - Myanmar Standard Time).<ref>{{cite web | url=https://restrictions.info/news/detail/3537 | title=Myanmar - restriction update 30.03.2020 06:52 UTC: COVID-19 Travel Restrictions Database}}</ref>\n*{{flag|North Korea}}: Closed its borders to all international tourists on January 21, 2020, one of the first countries to do so. Chinese visitors make up the bulk of foreign tourists to North Korea.<ref name=\"20200121reuters\" /> Also tightened/closed their border with mainland China.<ref name=\"newsweek1484978\" />\n*{{flag|Oman}}: Suspended tourist visas for all visitors, effective March 15, 2020, for 1 month.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://gulfbusiness.com/oman-suspends-tourist-visas-halts-sports-activities-for-month/|title=Oman suspends tourist visas, halts sports activities for month|date=March 12, 2020|website=Gulf Business}}</ref> Moreover, all cruise ships will be prevented from entering Omani ports [https://www.omanonlinevisa.com/restricted-entry-to-oman/ for 1 month].\n*{{flag|Pakistan}}: Closed its airports for both arrivals and departures on 21 March 2020 for two weeks. The date was later postponed to 11 April 2020.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/03/coronavirus-travel-restrictions-border-shutdowns-country-200318091505922.html|title=Coronavirus: Travel restrictions, border shutdowns by country|date=April 5, 2020|website=Al Jazeera}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Palestine}}: Tourist ban of West Bank from March 5, 2020 for 14 days.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.france24.com/en/20200305-palestinians-announce-west-bank-tourism-ban-over-coronavirus|title=Palestinians announce West Bank tourism ban over coronavirus|date=March 5, 2020|website=France 24}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Philippines}}: Visa issuance and visa-free entry for all foreign nationals are temporarily suspended as of March 19, 2020.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://globalnation.inquirer.net/186199/fwd-ph-temporarily-suspends-visa-issuance-visa-free-entry-of-all-foreign-nationals/amp|title=PH temporarily suspends visa issuance, visa-free entry to all foreign nationals|date=March 19, 2020|work=Philippine Daily Inquirer}}</ref> On March 22, all foreign visitors are barred from entry, with exceptions for foreign spouses and children of Filipino citizens, diplomatic officials, and workers for international organizations.<ref>{{cite web |title=Press Release: BI to implement DFA circular on suspension of arrivals |url=http://immigration.gov.ph/images/News/2020_Yr/03_Mar/2020Mar20b_Press.pdf |publisher=Bureau of Immigration |location=Philippines |format=PDF |date=March 20, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Cordero |first1=Ted |title=Foreigners banned from entering Philippines starting March 22 \u2013 DOTr |url=https://www.gmanetwork.com/news/news/nation/730560/foreigners-banned-from-entering-philippines-starting-march-22-dotr/story/ |agency=GMA News |date=March 20, 2019}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Russia}}: Borders closed to foreigners with some exceptions, effective March 18 and until May 1.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/coronavirus-russia-border-close-flights-when-residents-latest-a9405131.html|title=Russia closes borders until May amid coronavirus pandemic|date=March 16, 2020|website=The Independent}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Saudi Arabia}}: All international flights suspended, except in exceptional cases, for a period of two weeks, as of March 15, 2020.<ref>The Kingdom\u2019s government has decided to suspend international flights, except in exceptional cases for a period of two weeks, as of March 15 at 11:00.</ref> The Saudi Ministry of Foreign Affairs recently issued a statement announcing that all religious visits (Umrah) to the sacred Muslim sites of Mecca and Medina [https://www.saudiarabiavisa.com/entry-restrictions/ have to be cancelled or postponed for the time being].\n*{{flag|Singapore}}: All foreigners are prohibited to entry and transit starting from 23 March, 11.59pm. Only people working in essential services like healthcare services and transport will be allowed into Singapore during this time.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Toh |first1=Ting Wei |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/health/coronavirus-all-short-term-visitors-barred-from-entering-and-transiting-in |title=Coronavirus: All short-term visitors barred from entering and transiting in Singapore from Monday, 11.59pm |website=The Straits Times |access-date=22 March 2020 |date=22 March 2020}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Taiwan}}: Effective 19 March, non-citizens are prohibited to enter unless specifically approved.<ref>{{cite web |title=3\u67085\u65e5\u81f314\u65e5\u81ea\u6b50\u6d32\u5165\u5883\u6c11\u773e\u8acb\u5118\u901f\u901a\u5831\u9109\u93ae\u516c\u6240\uff1b\u53e6\u91dd\u5c0d\u6240\u6709\u975e\u672c\u570b\u7c4d\u4eba\u58eb\u9650\u5236\u5165\u5883\uff0c\u6240\u6709\u5165\u5883\u8005\u5165\u5883\u5f8c\u90fd\u9700\u9032\u884c\u5c45\u5bb6\u6aa2\u75ab14\u5929 |url=https://www.cdc.gov.tw/Bulletin/Detail/mwGBh07PQ_2FeJvl9xhfZw?typeid=9 |website=www.cdc.gov.tw |accessdate=18 March 2020 |language=zh-Hant}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Thailand}}: Effective March 26, 2020, passengers are not allowed to enter Thailand except airline crew with pre-existing schedules, diplomats and their family members, passengers with a work permit and passengers with a waiver from PM or PIC of State of Emergency.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://restrictions.info/news/detail/3365 | title=Thailand - restriction update 26.03.2020 00:56 UTC: COVID-19 Travel Restrictions Database}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Turkey}}: Effective March 28, Turkey is suspending all international flights to and from Turkey, amid [[COVID-19]] outbreak. Turkey also closed its borders with all its neighbours.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.aa.com.tr/en/latest-on-coronavirus-outbreak/turkey-cancels-all-int-l-flights-amid-covid-19-outbreak/1782602|title=Turkey cancels all int\u2019l flights amid COVID-19 outbreak|date=March 27, 2020|website=Anadolu Agency}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.aa.com.tr/en/turkey/turkey-closes-border-gates-with-greece-bulgaria/1770793|title=Turkey closes border gates with Greece, Bulgaria|date=March 27, 2020|website=Anadolu Agency}}</ref>\n* {{flag|Turkmenistan}}: In order to prevent the spread of coronavirus from March 20 to April 20, 2020, the national border of Turkmenistan is restricted to foreign citizens and stateless persons. If necessary, during the specified period, the following categories of persons can enter the territory of Turkmenistan in accordance with applicable norms and rules: diplomats of foreign countries, representatives of international organizations, crews of aircraft and ships, freight transport drivers engaged in international transit transport, members of work crews on railway ways and foreign representatives working at business facilities; located in the territory of Turkmenistan.<ref>[https://turkmenportal.com/blog/26238/turkmenistan-usilivaet-mery-po-predotvrashcheniyu-proniknoveniya-koronavirusa \u0422\u0443\u0440\u043a\u043c\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0430\u043d \u0443\u0441\u0438\u043b\u0438\u0432\u0430\u0435\u0442 \u043c\u0435\u0440\u044b \u043f\u043e \u043f\u0440\u0435\u0434\u043e\u0442\u0432\u0440\u0430\u0449\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044e \u043f\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0438\u043a\u043d\u043e\u0432\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0430]</ref>\n*{{flag|UAE}}: Effective March 19, 2020, passengers are not allowed to enter United Arab Emirates except family members (including father, mother, son, daughter, wife, husband, grandparents, grandchildren and domestic helpers) of nationals of United Arab Emirates.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://restrictions.info/news/detail/2326 | title=United Arab Emirates - restriction update 19.03.2020 15:48 UTC: COVID-19 Travel Restrictions Database}}</ref> Effective March 25, 2020, flights to United Arab Emirates are suspended from 24 March 2020 23:59 Local Time until 7 April 2020 23:59 Local Time.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://restrictions.info/news/detail/3193 | title=United Arab Emirates - restriction update 24.03.2020 22:16 UTC: COVID-19 Travel Restrictions Database}}</ref>. All visas to foreigners except diplomatic passport holders, with effect from 17 March 2020 have been invalidated. The decision does not apply to those who already have their visas issued prior to the aforementioned date, and visa on arrival is still available for a large number of countries.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dubaiairports.ae/alert/latest-covid-19-update|title=March 17, 2020 Latest Covid-19 Update|date=2020-03-16}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://gulfbusiness.com/uae-suspends-issuance-of-all-visas-bans-travel-to-italy-turkey-among-others/|title=UAE suspends issuance of all visas, bans travel to Italy, Turkey, among others|date=March 14, 2020|website=Gulf Business}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Vietnam}}: Effective 22 March 2020, Entry of all foreigners is suspended until further notice. Temporary suspension of entry will also be applied to all overseas Vietnamese and their spouses and children who have been granted with certificate of visa exemption.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://news.chinhphu.vn/Home/BREAKING-VN-to-halt-entry-to-all-foreigners-since-March-22-due-to-COVID19/20203/39326.vgp |title = VGP News &#124; VN HALTS entry to all foreigners due to COVID-19 - VN HALTS entry to all foreigners due to COVID-19}}</ref>\n\n=== Africa ===\n* {{flag|Cape Verde}}: On 17 March, as a contingency measure, Prime Minister [[Jos\u00e9 Ulisses Correia e Silva]] announced<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.cnn.com/travel/article/coronavirus-travel-bans/index.html |title=Coronavirus: Which countries have travel bans?|work=CNN |last=O'Hare |first=Maureen |last2=Hardingham |first2=Tamara |last-author-amp=y |date=17 March 2020 |accessdate=17 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.governo.cv/covid19-governo-declara-situacao-de-contingencia-a-nivel-da-protecao-civil/ |title=COVID19: Governo declara situa\u00e7\u00e3o de conting\u00eancia a n\u00edvel da Prote\u00e7\u00e3o Civil |publisher=Governo de Cabo Verde |language=Portuguese |date=17 March 2020 |access-date=20 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.rtc.cv/tcv/index.php?paginas=47&id_cod=89239 |work=TCV |title=Governo declara situa\u00e7\u00e3o de conting\u00eancia, a n\u00edvel de Prote\u00e7\u00e3o Civil, por causa do Covid-19 |language=Portuguese |date=17 March 2020 |access-date=20 March 2020}}</ref> the suspension of all incoming flights from the [[United States|US]], [[Brazil]], [[Senegal]], [[Nigeria]], [[Portugal]], and all [[Europe]]an countries affected by the coronavirus. Since at the time Cape Verde had no air travel connections to other countries, in practice, this results in a lockdown.\n* {{flag|Cote d'Ivoire}}<ref name=\"iatatravelcentre.com\"/>\n* {{flag|Egypt}}: Egypt's Prime Minister Moustafa Madbouly announced that Egypt will be shutting down its airports and air travel starting from Thursday March 19 at noon until April 15 to prevent the spread of the coronavirus.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://egyptianstreets.com/2020/03/16/egypt-shuts-down-airports-suspends-air-travel-pm/|title=Egypt Shuts Down Airports, Suspends Air Travel: PM|date=March 16, 2020}}</ref>\n* {{flag|The Gambia}}: Closed its sole land border with [[Senegal]], and closed its airspace to most flights.<ref>{{cite news |title=COVID-19: Gambia, Senegal to close border for 21 days |url=https://www.aa.com.tr/en/africa/covid-19-gambia-senegal-to-close-border-for-21-days/1776298 |accessdate=1 April 2020}}</ref>\n* {{flag|Ghana}}: Effective March 17, 2020 Ghana will ban anyone that has been to a country with more than 200 cases in the previous 14 days, unless they are an official resident or a Ghanaian national. Citizens and resident-permit holders will be required to self-isolate for 14 days on arrival.<ref>[https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2020-03-15/ghana-closes-borders-for-arrivals-from-coronavirus-hit-countries Bloomberg - Are you a robot?<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>\n* {{flag|Kenya}}: Effective March 17, 2020 Kenya halted the entry of foreigners from countries that have confirmed coronavirus cases. Only Kenyan citizens, and any foreigners with valid residence permits will be allowed to come in provided they proceed on self-quarantine or to a government designated quarantine facility.<ref>[https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2020-03-15/kenya-restricts-foreign-travel-suspends-school-on-coronavirus Bloomberg - Are you a robot?<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>\n*{{flag|Madagascar}}: All flights to Madagascar are suspended until 20 April 2020.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://restrictions.info/news/detail/3609 | title=Madagascar - restriction update 01.04.2020 12:24 UTC: COVID-19 Travel Restrictions Database}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Mauritius}}: Passengers are not allowed to transit or enter Mauritius.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://restrictions.info/news/detail/3615 | title=Mauritius - restriction update 01.04.2020 21:44 UTC: COVID-19 Travel Restrictions Database}}</ref>\n* {{flag|Morocco}}: On March 15, 2020 Morocco suspended all international passenger flights to and from the country.<ref>{{cite web|author=Kirsten Donovan|date=March 15, 2020|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-morocco-flights/morocco-suspends-all-international-passenger-flights-foreign-ministry-idUSKBN2120QQ|title=Morocco suspends all international passenger flights - foreign ministry|trans-title=|language=en|website=reuters.com}}</ref>\n* {{flag|Nigeria}}: On March 26, 2020 Nigeria ordered the immediate closure of international airports and land borders for a period of four weeks.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vanguardngr.com/2020/03/breaking-buhari-directs-closure-of-air-land-borders-for-4-weeks|title=BREAKING: Buhari directs closure of air, land borders for 4 weeks|last=Ogunyinka|first=Victor|date=26 March 2020|accessdate=26 March 2020|publisher=[[Vanguard (Nigeria)|Vanguard Newspaper]]}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Seychelles}}: Effective 30 March 2020, Passengers are not allowed to enter Seychelles except specified categoried of passengers.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://restrictions.info/news/detail/3539 | title=Seychelles - restriction update 30.03.2020 08:10 UTC: COVID-19 Travel Restrictions Database}}</ref>\n* {{flag|South Africa}}: Ban on entry to travellers who have been in UK, US, Italy, Iran, South Korea, Spain, Germany in the 20 days before arrival. Suspension of visa on arrival scheme, and no entry without a visa. Some flights suspended form 21 March. Travellers in the country who received a stamp on arrival allowing them to stay for 90 days do not need to apply for a visa. UK travellers only permitted entry if transiting home, but there is a ban on both entry and transit to travellers who have been in China, France, Germany, Iran, Italy, South Korea, Spain, Switzerland, USA or United Kingdom, since 15 March.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/travel/2020/mar/23/coronavirus-travel-updates-which-countries-have-restrictions-and-fco-warnings-in-place\n|title=Coronavirus travel updates: which countries have restrictions and FCO warnings in place?\n|website=www.theguardian.com|date=March 23, 2020}}</ref>\n* {{flag|Sudan}}: Effective March 17, 2020 Sudan declared a state of emergency and closed all airports and land borders, this after one person died of COVID-19 in the country.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.europapress.es/internacional/noticia-sudan-declara-estado-emergencia-sanitaria-cierra-puertos-aeropuertos-cruces-fronterizos-coronavirus-20200316193257.html|title=Sud\u00e1n declara el \"estado de emergencia sanitaria\" y cierra puertos, aeropuertos y cruces fronterizos por el coronavirus|first=Europa|last=Press|date=March 16, 2020|website=www.europapress.es}}</ref>\n\n=== Americas ===\n*{{flag|Argentina}}: Borders closed to non-residents, effective March 15.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.batimes.com.ar/news/argentina/argentina-to-close-schools-for-two-weeks-borders-to-visitors.phtml|title=Buenos Aires Times &#124; Argentina to close schools for two weeks, borders to visitors|website=www.batimes.com.ar}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Belize}}: Borders closed to all travellers, including Belizean nationals except for emergency situations.<ref>{{cite news |title=All borders closed to the entry of Belizean nationals |url=https://www.breakingbelizenews.com/2020/04/05/all-borders-closed-to-the-entry-of-belizean-nationals/ |accessdate=6 April 2020 |work=Breaking Belize News-The Leading Online News Source of Belize |date=5 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Belize is now on war footing; PM Barrow announces closure of borders to national |url=https://www.breakingbelizenews.com/2020/04/03/belize-is-now-on-war-footing-pm-barrow-announces-closure-of-borders-to-national/ |accessdate=6 April 2020 |work=Breaking Belize News-The Leading Online News Source of Belize |date=3 April 2020}}</ref>\n* {{flag|Bermuda}}: Effective March 20, 2020, a travel ban will be in place to disallow travelers to Bermuda unless the person is a Bermuda resident, a crew member, or a person with the written permission of the Quarantine Authority of Bermuda to enter.<ref>{{Citation | url = https://www.gov.bm/coronavirus | title = Novel Coronavirus (COVID-19) - Information for Travellers | date = 10 March 2020 | publisher = Govenment of Bermuda | accessdate = 2020-03-20}}</ref> Flights to Bermuda are suspended until 1 May 2020.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://restrictions.info/news/detail/3740 | title=Bermuda - restriction update 02.04.2020 20:50 UTC: COVID-19 Travel Restrictions Database}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Bolivia}}: Effective March 20, Borders closed to foreigners and international flights cancelled.<ref>[https://www.lostiempos.com/actualidad/pais/20200317/bolivia-cierra-fronteras-suspende-vuelos-limita-transporte-terrestre Bolivia cierra fronteras, suspende vuelos y limita el transporte terrestre por el coronavirus | Los Tiempos<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>\n*{{flag|Brazil}}: Effective March 30, 2020, passengers are not allowed to enter Brazil except specific categories of passengers.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://restrictions.info/news/detail/3536 | title=Brazil - restrictions update 30.03.2020: COVID-19 Travel Restrictions Database}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Canada}}: Borders are closed to all travelers who are not citizens, permanent residents or U.S. citizens. Exceptions are placed for diplomats, crew and immediate family members of citizens with clearing a basic health assessment by air operators.<ref>{{cite news | url=https://www.cbc.ca/news/politics/cbsa-border-airports-screening-trudeau-covid19-coronavirus-1.5498866 |title = Canada to bar entry to travellers who are not citizens, permanent residents or Americans | work = CBC News | date = March 16, 2020 | accessdate = March 20, 2020}}</ref> The U.S. and Canada later agreed to close the [[Canada\u2013United States border]] to non-essential traffic.<ref>{{Cite news | url = https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2020-03-18/trump-says-u-s-canada-close-their-border-after-virus-spreads | title = U.S., Canada Agree to Block Leisure Travel Between the Countries | work = [[Bloomberg News]] | date = March 18, 2020 | accessdate = March 18, 2020}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Chile}}: Passengers are not allowed to enter Chile.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://restrictions.info/news/detail/3891 | title=Chile - restriction update 04.04.2020 00:36 UTC: COVID-19 Travel Restrictions Database}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Costa Rica}}: Borders closed to non-residents, effective March 16 through April 12. Exceptions in place for crews. All returning nationals and residents are subject to mandatory 14 day quarantine.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nacion.com/el-pais/salud/nuevo-coronavirus-en-costa-rica-gobierno-decreta/FWLVLR5NSZDZ3FKVHHWXYQSCHI/story/|title=Nuevo coronavirus en Costa Rica: Gobierno decreta estado de emergencia nacional|website=La Naci\u00f3n, Grupo Naci\u00f3n}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Colombia}}: Effective 17 March, Colombia will close borders completely until May 30. Cargo will be permitted, but no persons will be allowed to enter or exit.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.portafolio.co/economia/gobierno/colombia-cierra-sus-fronteras-539113|title=Colombia cierra sus fronteras durante los pr\u00f3ximos 75 d\u00edas|date=March 16, 2020|via=www.portfolio.co}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Cuba}}: Effective March 24, 2020, Borders closed to all non-residents; only Cuban and foreign residents will be allowed to enter the country.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://adncuba.com/noticias-de-cuba/cuba-anuncia-cierre-de-frontera-solo-podran-entrar-cubanos-y-extranjeros |title = Cuba anuncia cierre de frontera: Solo podr\u00e1n entrar cubanos y extranjeros residentes}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-cuba-president/cuba-bars-entry-to-foreign-tourists-in-bid-to-contain-coronavirus-spread-idUSKBN2173NC|title=Cuba bars entry to foreign tourists in bid to contain coronavirus spread|newspaper=Reuters|date=March 20, 2020|accessdate = March 21, 2020 |via=www.reuters.com}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Dominica}}: Suspended all flights.<ref>{{cite news |title=Coronavirus: Travel restrictions, border shutdowns by country |url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/03/coronavirus-travel-restrictions-border-shutdowns-country-200318091505922.html |accessdate=1 April 2020 |work=www.aljazeera.com}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Dominican Republic}}: The President of the Dominican Republic ordered to close all borders, effective March 19.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nydailynews.com/news/politics/ny-dominican-coronavirus-20200318-fedw3a473zcz5jkwh5d2xco4um-story.html|title=Dominican Republic closes borders over coronavirus, halts all incoming flights|date=March 18, 2020|via=www.nydailynews.com}}</ref> Flights to Dominican Rep. are suspended until 12 April 2020.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://restrictions.info/news/detail/3594 | title=Dominican Republic - restriction update 31.03.2020 15:56 UTC: COVID-19 Travel Restrictions Database}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Ecuador}}: Effective 25 March 2020, Ecuador's borders are closed, flights to Ecuador are suspended until 5 April 2020.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://restrictions.info/tr/country/ec/ | title=Travel restrictions of Ecuador: COVID-19 Travel Restrictions Database}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=https://restrictions.info/news/detail/3195 | title=Travel restrictions update for Ecuador - 25.03.2020: COVID-19 Travel Restrictions Database}}</ref>\n*{{flag|El Salvador}}: On March 11, the President of El Salvador announced an Executive Order barring the entry of foreigners.<ref name=\"elsalvador.1\">{{cite web|url=https://sv.usembassy.gov/health-alert-u-s-embassy-san-salvador-el-salvador-march-12-2020/|title=Health Alert \u2013 U.S. Embassy San Salvador, El Salvador &#124; U.S. Embassy in El Salvador|date=March 12, 2020|website=U.S. Embassy in \u00a0 El\u00a0Salvador}}</ref> The General Directorate of Migration will deny entry to all foreigners, excluding accredited diplomats and legal residents of El Salvador.<ref name=\"elsalvador.1\" />\n*{{flag|Guatemala}}: The Guatemalan Government announced on March 16 that the country was closing its borders for two weeks, starting on midnight March 17.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/article/coronavirus-travel-restrictions.html|title=Coronavirus Travel Restrictions, Across the Globe|website=The New York Times|accessdate=March 17, 2020}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Guyana}}: Airports in Guyana are closed to all international passenger flights until 1 May 2020.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://restrictions.info/news/detail/3893 | title=Guyana - restriction update 04.04.2020 11:22 UTC: COVID-19 Travel Restrictions Database}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Honduras}}: Borders closed to all traffic, aside from the movement of goods, effective March 15, 23:59.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://hn.usembassy.gov/covid-19-information/|title=COVID-19 Information|date=March 26, 2020|website=U.S. Embassy in Honduras}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Jamaica}}: No entry except by government authorization.<ref name=\"iatatravelcentre.com\"/>\n*{{flag|Panama}}: From 11.59 p.m on Monday night (March 16), only Panamanians and foreign residents would be allowed to enter Panama.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.garda.com/crisis24/news-alerts/323071/panama-authorities-prohibit-all-foreigners-from-entering-the-country-due-to-covid-19-march-16-update-3 |title=Panama: Authorities prohibit all foreigners from entering the country due to COVID-19 March 16 /update 3 |publisher=Garda.com |date=2020-03-16 |accessdate=2020-03-30}}</ref> From 11.59 pm on Sunday 22 March, all international flights will be halted.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gov.uk/foreign-travel-advice/panama/coronavirus|title=Foreign travel advice: Panama|last=|first=|date=2020|website=gov.uk|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=March 26, 2020}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Paraguay}}: Flights to Paraguay are suspended until 12 April 2020.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://restrictions.info/tr/country/py/ | title=Travel restrictions of Paraguay: COVID-19 Travel Restrictions Database}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=https://restrictions.info/news/detail/3226 | title=Travel restrictions update for Paraguay - 25.03.2020: COVID-19 Travel Restrictions Database}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Peru}}: Peru restricts access to the interior of the country from 12:00 on March 17.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://gestion.pe/peru/coronavirus-en-peru-presidente-martin-vizcarra-anuncia-cierre-de-todas-las-fronteras-durante-estado-de-emergencia-nndc-noticia/|title=Per\u00fa anuncia el cierre de todas sus fronteras para evitar el avance de coronavirus: Vigente desde el martes|first=Redacci\u00f3n|last=Gesti\u00f3n|date=March 16, 2020|website=Gesti\u00f3n}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Suriname}}: Will close its borders for all persons and flights starting March 14.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-suriname-confirmed/suriname-confirms-first-coronavirus-case-authorities-will-close-borders-idUSKBN210373 |title=Suriname confirms first coronavirus case, authorities will close borders |date=13 March 2020 |work=Reuters |access-date=13 March 2020 |via=www.reuters.com}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Trinidad and Tobago}}: On March 16, Trinidad and Tobago announced that it closed its borders to all except Trinidad and Tobago nationals and certain medical personnel,<ref>{{Cite news|last=Nanton|first=Sampson|url=http://www.guardian.co.tt/news/tt-shuts-down-borders-bars-to-be-closed-6.2.1080079.6b07bec899|title=T&T shuts down borders, bars to be closed|date=2020-03-16|work=Trinidad and Tobago Guardian|access-date=2020-03-16|url-status=live}}</ref> by midnight on March 17.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Clyne|first=Kalifa Sarah|url=https://newsday.co.tt/2020/03/16/government-shuts-tt-borders/|title=Government shuts TT borders|date=2020-03-16|work=Trinidad and Tobago Newsday|access-date=2020-03-16|url-status=live}}</ref> Airports in Trinidad and Tobago are closed until 30 April 2020.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://restrictions.info/news/detail/3541 | title=Trinidad and Tobago - restriction update 30.03.2020 09:18 UTC: COVID-19 Travel Restrictions Database}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Uruguay}}<ref>{{cite news |title=Cierre total de fronteras para extranjeros, salvo en ciudades de frontera con Brasil |url=https://www.subrayado.com.uy/uruguay-resuelve-el-cierre-absoluto-fronteras-extranjeros-ciudades-fronterizas-brasil-n614022 |accessdate=5 April 2020 |work=subrayado.com.uy |language=es-ES}}</ref>\n\n=== Europe ===\n* {{flag|European Union}}: The European Council agreed on March 17 to ban incoming travel other than citizens from countries in the [[European Union]], [[European Economic Area]], Switzerland and United Kingdom, [[Long-term resident (European Union)|long-term residents]] and people with long-term visa or residence permits, family members of EU and EEA citizens, medical personnel and people responsible for transport of goods for 30 days.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.consilium.europa.eu/en/meetings/european-council/2020/03/17/ |title = Video conference of the members of the European Council, 17 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.politico.eu/article/the-eu-european-union-coronavirus-covid19-travel-ban-explained/ |title = The EU travel ban explained|date = 17 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.europapress.es/internacional/noticia-lideres-europeos-aceptan-cerrar-fronteras-exteriores-ue-viajes-esenciales-20200317203959.html|title=Los l\u00edderes europeos aceptan cerrar las fronteras exteriores de la UE salvo para viajes \"esenciales\"|first=Europa|last=Press|date=March 17, 2020|website=www.europapress.es}}</ref> Each country has to implement the decision on the national level. Ireland choose to opt out from the decision due to the [[Common Travel Area]]. The agreement was to close borders for 30 days starting at noon on March 17, though enforcement did not begin immediately as planned.<ref>[https://www.schengenvisainfo.com/news/breaking-eu-decides-to-close-all-schengen-borders-for-30-days/ BREAKING: EU Decides to Close All Schengen Borders For 30 Days]</ref> By the end of March, all EU member states (except Ireland) and all associated Schengen states (Iceland, Liechtenstein, Norway and Switzerland) had introduced the travel restriction.<ref>[https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/PDF/?uri=CELEX:52020XC0330(02)]</ref> Some member states choose to go further and also prohibited EU and EEA citizens from entering, unless they are permanently living in the country or transiting to their home country.\n*{{flag|Austria}}: Closed borders for persons not having medical certificate confirming negative test for SARS-CoV-2, not older than four days upon entry.<ref>{{cite web |title=Grenzkontrollma\u00dfnahmen an \u00d6sterreichs Grenzen |url=https://bmi.gv.at/news.aspx?id=314A5A707A4547684D55733D |website=bmi.gv.at |accessdate=2 April 2020 |language=de}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Belgium}}: Closed its borders to non-essential travel on March 20.<ref>{{cite web |title=Belgian borders shut to non-essential travel |url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/world/belgian-borders-shut-to-non-essential-travel-12562392 |website=CNA |accessdate=2 April 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Croatia}}: Closed its borders to non-citizens on March 19.<ref>{{cite web |title=Croatia imposes new restrictions concerning cross-border traffic |url=https://www.croatiaweek.com/croatia-imposes-new-restrictions-concerning-cross-border-traffic/ |website=Croatia Week |accessdate=5 April 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Czech Republic}}: Partially closed its borders on March 14. Closed its borders to all non-residents on March 16.<ref name=\"czech.1\">{{cite web|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=2020_coronavirus_pandemic_in_the_Czech_Republic&oldid=945894827|title=2020 coronavirus pandemic in the Czech Republic|date=March 16, 2020|via=Wikipedia}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Denmark}}: Closed its borders to all non-citizens March 14.<ref name=\"denmark.1\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/health-coronavirus-denmark-idUSL8N2B673O|title=Denmark shutting its borders to curb spread of coronavirus, prime minister says|newspaper=Reuters|date=March 13, 2020|via=www.reuters.com}}</ref>  This includes a ban on crossing the border for all tourism, but exempts travellers with \"credible purpose\" such as non-citizen Danish residents.<ref name=\"denmark.1\" />\n*{{flag|Estonia}}: Effective March 17, 2020, foreign travelers are not allowed to enter. Right of entry will remain for citizens and those with a right of residence, and foreign citizens whose next of kin live in Estonia. Transit is allowed for foreigners not showing signs of the coronavirus. A mandatory two-week quarantine will be set for anyone entering the country.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.err.ee/1064173/estonia-to-close-borders-to-foreign-nationals-from-march-17|title=Estonia to close borders to foreign nationals from March 17|date=March 15, 2020|website=ERR}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Finland}}: Closed its borders on March 19, 2020, except for Finnish citizens returning to Finland, foreigners returning to their countries of origin, essential work-related travel, and goods. Finnish citizens returning home are recommended to quarantine themselves for 14 days after arrival.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://yle.fi/uutiset/3-11262175|title=Muutokset astuvat voimaan: Koronaviruksen aiheuttama poikkeustila sulkee koulut t\u00e4n\u00e4\u00e4n, rajat kiinni torstaina|date=March 18, 2020|website=Yle|access-date=March 20, 2020|language=fi}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Hungary}}: Hungary closed its borders for all passenger transport on March 17 and only Hungarian citizens and permanent residents are allowed to enter.<ref>{{cite web |title=Borders Closed: Who Can Enter Hungary and How? |url=https://hungarytoday.hu/borders-closed-who-can-enter-hungary-and-how/ |website=Hungary Today |accessdate=5 April 2020 |language=en |date=17 March 2020}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Latvia}}: Effective March 17, 2020 all international passenger connections by air, railway, sea and road, were be cancelled. Only Latvians and foreigners with residency rights in Latvia will be able to enter the country from outside the Schengen Area,<ref>{{cite web |title=Emergency situation in Latvia to restrict the spread of Covid-19 |url=https://www.mfa.gov.lv/en/consular-information/news/65754-emergency-situation-declared-throughout-the-national-territory-until-14-april-2020-to-restrict-the-spread-of-covid-19 |website=Ministry of Foreign Affairs of the Republic of Latvia |accessdate=27 March 2020 |date=17 March 2020}}</ref> but entry of foreign citizens by private vehicle from other Schengen member countries was still allowed.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://eng.lsm.lv/article/society/health/latvia-to-close-borders-to-passenger-traffic-on-tuesday-17-march.a351774/|title=Latvia to close borders to passenger traffic on Tuesday 17 March|date=2020-03-14|work=LSM.LV|access-date=2020-03-26|language=en}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Lithuania}}: Closed the border for foreigners, except for those with residence permits, effective 00:00 (UTC+02:00) March 16 \u2013 April 13, 2020.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://lrv.lt/lt/naujienos/vyriausybe-nusprende-karantinas-tesiamas-iki-balandzio-13-dienos|title=Vyriausyb\u0117 nusprend\u0117: karantinas t\u0119siamas iki baland\u017eio 13 dienos|date=2020-03-25}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Norway}}: Effective March 16, 2020, closed airports temporarily. Foreigners are turned away, and exemptions are made for Norwegians returning from abroad, and for goods.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://uk.reuters.com/article/uk-health-coronavirus-norway-airport-idUKKBN2110Z0|title=Norway to close ports, airports from Monday to stop coronavirus - PM|date=2020-03-14|work=Reuters|access-date=2020-03-15|language=en}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Moldova}}: Closed its airspace and terrestrial borders for all foreigners, except for diplomats and permanent residents, effective from 00:00 (UTC+02:00) March 17, 2020.<ref>[https://tass.ru/obschestvo/7984033 \u041c\u043e\u043b\u0434\u0430\u0432\u0438\u044f \u0437\u0430\u043a\u0440\u044b\u0432\u0430\u0435\u0442 \u0433\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0446\u0443 \u0438\u0437-\u0437\u0430 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0430 \u0441 17 \u043c\u0430\u0440\u0442\u0430]. tass.ru (15 March 2020)</ref>\n*{{flag|Poland}}: Effective March 15 \u2013 April 11, 2020, entry ban for all foreigners except for those with residential or work permits, and 14 days' quarantine on all people entering.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-poland-foreigners-idUSKBN21031F|title=Poland to close borders to foreigners, quarantine returnees|newspaper=Reuters|date=March 13, 2020|via=www.reuters.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gov.pl/web/koronawirus/zamykamy-granice-przed-koronawirusem|title=Zamykamy granice przed koronawirusem|date=2020-03-13|via =www.Gov.pl}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gov.pl/web/koronawirus/pytania-i-odpowiedzi|title=Najcz\u0119\u015bciej zadawane pytania|via =www.Gov.pl}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Romania}}: Effective March 22, 2020 Romania banned foreign citizens from entering the country with the exception of official residents or those who are transiting the country.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.romania-insider.com/coronavirus-romania-borders-malls-closed|title=Coronavirus in Romania: Country closes borders for foreign citizens, malls close, people's movement and religious service restricted|website=Romania Insider|language=en|access-date=2020-03-25}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Russia}}: Borders closed to foreigners with some exceptions, effective March 18 and until May 1.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/coronavirus-russia-border-close-flights-when-residents-latest-a9405131.html|title=Russia closes borders until May amid coronavirus pandemic|date=March 16, 2020|website=The Independent}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Serbia}}: Closed its borders on March 16.<ref>{{cite web |title=Serbia closes its borders to foreigners over coronavirus |url=https://www.euractiv.com/section/justice-home-affairs/news/serbia-closes-its-borders-to-foreigners-over-coronavirus/ |website=www.euractiv.com |accessdate=3 April 2020 |date=16 March 2020}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Slovakia}}: Closed its borders to all nonresidents on March 13.<ref name=\"slovakia.1\">[https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2020-03-12/slovakia-closes-borders-for-non-residents-to-fight-coronavirus Bloomberg - Are you a robot?<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>  Closed international airports and require all residents returning from abroad to quarantine.<ref name=\"slovakia.1\" />  Violators may be fined up to 1659 EUR.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uvzsr.sk/index.php?view=article&id=4087|title=COVID-19: \u00dastredn\u00fd kr\u00edzov\u00fd \u0161t\u00e1b zav\u00e1dza \u010fal\u0161ie opatrenia, zatvoria sa \u0161koly i\u00a0letisk\u00e1, karant\u00e9na plat\u00ed pre v\u0161etk\u00fdch, ktor\u00ed sa vr\u00e1tia zo zahrani\u010dia|website=www.uvzsr.sk}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Spain}}: Closed borders to non-residents on March 17.<ref>{{cite web |title=Spain closes its borders to contain spread of coronavirus |url=https://english.elpais.com/society/2020-03-16/spain-closes-its-borders-to-contain-coronavirus.html |website=EL PA\u00cdS |accessdate=3 April 2020 |language=en |date=16 March 2020}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Switzerland}}: Borders closed to foreigners, starting 17 March 2020.\n*{{flag|Turkey}}: Effective March 28, Turkey is suspending all international flights to and from Turkey, amid [[COVID-19]] outbreak. Turkey also closed its borders with all its neighbours.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.aa.com.tr/en/latest-on-coronavirus-outbreak/turkey-cancels-all-int-l-flights-amid-covid-19-outbreak/1782602|title=Turkey cancels all int\u2019l flights amid COVID-19 outbreak|date=March 27, 2020|website=Anadolu Agency}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.aa.com.tr/en/turkey/turkey-closes-border-gates-with-greece-bulgaria/1770793|title=Turkey closes border gates with Greece, Bulgaria|date=March 27, 2020|website=Anadolu Agency}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Ukraine}}: Starting March 15, Ukraine has closed its border for foreigners for two weeks. Returning Ukrainian citizens will be required to submit to health observation procedures.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://112.international/ukraine-top-news/ukraine-closing-border-for-foreigners-for-two-weeks-49475.html|title=Ukraine closing border for foreigners for two weeks|website=112.international}}</ref> Effective March 17, Ukraine is suspending all commercial passenger services, including flights, trains and passenger buses, to and from Ukraine for a period of two weeks.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ua.usembassy.gov/covid-19-information/|title=COVID-19 Information|date=March 13, 2020|website=U.S. Embassy in Ukraine}}</ref>\n\n===Oceania===\n* {{flag|Australia}}: Borders closed to all non-citizens or permanent residents from 21:00 March 20.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.abc.net.au/news/2020-03-19/coronavirus-non-resident-travel-ban-australia/12071640|title=Australia blocks arrival of all non-residents in expanded coronavirus travel ban|accessdate=March 19, 2020}}</ref>\n* {{flag|Marshall Islands}}: Passengers are not allowed to enter Marshall Isl. until 5 May 2020.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://restrictions.info/tr/country/mh/ | title=Travel restrictions of Marshall Islands: COVID-19 Travel Restrictions Database}}</ref>\n* {{flag|New Caledonia}}: Passengers except parents of a French minor and spouses of a national of France are not allowed to enter New Caledonia. Flights to New Caledonia are suspended until 31 May 2020.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://restrictions.info/news/detail/3605 | title=Travel restrictions of Vanuatu: COVID-19 Travel Restrictions Database}}</ref>\n* {{flag|New Zealand}}: Borders closed to all non-citizens or permanent residents including the previously exempt Pacific Islands or temporary visa holders (such as students) from 23:59 March 19.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.rnz.co.nz/news/national/412162/nz-to-close-its-borders-to-anyone-not-a-citizen-or-permanent-resident-pm-confirms|title=NZ to close its borders to anyone not a citizen or permanent resident., PM confirms|accessdate=March 19, 2020}}</ref>\n* {{flag|Fiji}}: Borders closed to all non-citizens.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.itij.com/latest/news/fiji-airways-suspends-95-cent-its-international-flights|title=Fiji closes borders|accessdate=March 22, 2020}}</ref>\n* {{flag|Tuvalu}}: Tuvalu's borders are closed.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://restrictions.info/tr/country/tv/ | title=Travel restrictions of Tuvalu: COVID-19 Travel Restrictions Database}}</ref>\n* {{flag|Vanuatu}}: Vanuatu ports of entry are closed from 20 March 2020.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://restrictions.info/tr/country/vu/ | title=Travel restrictions of Vanuatu: COVID-19 Travel Restrictions Database}}</ref>\n\n==Countries implementing global quarantine measures ==\n* {{flag|Australia}}: The Australian Government has announced that any person \u2013 regardless of citizenship or residency status \u2013 travelling to Australia from any international destination will be required to undergo a compulsory 14-day quarantine, beginning from their date of arrival. The regulations, effective from March 16, 2020, also ban cruise ships arriving from international waters from docking at any Australian port.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Wright |first1=Shane |title=PM introduces strict travel restrictions for all arrivals |url=https://www.smh.com.au/national/pm-introduces-strict-travel-restrictions-for-all-arrivals-20200315-p54a8q.html |work=The Sydney Morning Herald |date=15 March 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n* {{flag|Benin}}: 14-day quarantine.<ref name=\"iatatravelcentre.com\"/>\n*{{flag|Canada}}: Effective midnight March 25, 2020, the Canadian government announced an Emergency Order under the ''[[Quarantine Act, 2005|Quarantine Act]]'' that requires any person entering Canada by air, sea or land to self-isolate for 14 days whether or not they have symptoms of COVID-19.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.canada.ca/en/public-health/news/2020/03/new-order-makes-self-isolation-mandatory-for-individuals-entering-canada.html|title=New Order Makes Self-Isolation Mandatory for Individuals Entering Canada|date=March 25, 2020|website=Government of Canada}}</ref>\n* {{flag|Chile}}: Will not permit cruise ships to dock as of March 15. Travelers who have been to countries of concern are subject to examination or quarantine upon arrival.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://cl.usembassy.gov/covid-19-information/|title=COVID-19 in Chile: Information for American Citizens|date=March 5, 2020|website=U.S. Embassy in Chile}}</ref>\n* {{flag|Ethiopia}}: Mandatory 14-day quarantine at the traveller's expense.<ref name=\"iatatravelcentre.com\"/>\n* {{flag|Fiji}}: After the lockdown of [[Lautoka]] on 20 March 2020, no person regardless of citizenship is allowed to leave the confines of the city.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fbcnews.com.fj/news/covid-19/pm-no-exceptions-to-leave-lautoka-during-lockdown/|title=No exceptions to leave Lautoka|date=March 22, 2020|website=FBC}}</ref>\n* {{flag|Bailiwick of Guernsey|name=Guernsey}}: Imposed a requirement on all persons arriving in the Bailiwick from anywhere in the world (including Jersey and the UK) to self-isolate for 14 days on arrival. This is a legal requirement, and failure to comply is a criminal offence.<ref>[https://gov.gg/CHttpHandler.ashx?id=124043&p=0] 19 March 2020 \"www.gov.gg\", accessed 20 March 2020</ref>\n*{{flag|Hong Kong}}: Effective 19 March 2020, all persons arriving in Hong Kong who have been to Mainland China or any overseas countries/territories (excluding [[Macao]] and [[Taiwan]]) in the past 14 days, regardless of whether they are Hong Kong residents, are subject to compulsory quarantine.<ref>{{cite web |title=COVID-19 Thematic Website - Together, We Fight the Virus - Inbound Travel |url=https://www.coronavirus.gov.hk/eng/inbound-travel.html |publisher=Hong Kong SAR Government |accessdate=19 March 2020}}</ref> Effective 25 March 2020, all persons arriving in Hong Kong, regardless of whether they are Hong Kong residents, are subject to compulsory quarantine.<ref>{{cite web |title=HK to turn away many non-residents for 14 days |url=https://news.rthk.hk/rthk/en/component/k2/1516270-20200323.htm |publisher=RTHK |accessdate=23 March 2020}}</ref> \n* {{flag|Jersey}}: From Friday 20 March, all travellers arriving in Jersey must now self-isolate for 14 days. This includes the UK, Guernsey, Europe and the rest of the world.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gov.je/Health/Coronavirus/Pages/CoronavirusTravelAdvice.aspx |title=Travel advice for coronavirus (COVID-19) |publisher=Gov.je |date= |accessdate=2020-03-30}}</ref>\n* {{flag|Malta}}: Tourists entering Malta from any country from 13:30 on March 13, 2020 onwards must spend 14 days in mandatory quarantine, which 14 days start from the last day that they were in any of these countries. This is enforceable by law. Failure to observe this obligation will result in fines of \u20ac1,000 for each time it is breached.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.visitmalta.com/en/Covid-19|title=Visitmalta - The official tourism website for Malta, Gozo and Comino.|website=www.visitmalta.com}}</ref>\n* {{flag|New Zealand}}: Beginning March 15, any person travelling into New Zealand from overseas, including New Zealand citizens, will be required to self-isolate for 14 days following entry into the country, except for those travelling from the Pacific Islands unless they are displaying symptoms. All cruise ships have been banned entry into New Zealand until June 30.<ref name=\"tvnz15032020\">{{cite news|title=Everyone entering New Zealand will be required to isolate, cruise ships banned|url=https://www.tvnz.co.nz/one-news/new-zealand/covid-19-everyone-entering-new-zealand-required-isolate-cruise-ships-banned|accessdate=15 March 2020}}</ref> Beginning 23:59 on March 19, New Zealand will not permit any new arrivals to non-citizens or permanent residents including the previously excluded Pacific Islands and temporary visa holders.<ref>{{cite news|title=NZ to close its borders to anyone not a citizen or permanent resident., PM confirms|url=https://www.rnz.co.nz/news/national/412162/live-nz-to-close-its-borders-to-anyone-not-a-citizen-or-permanent-resident-pm-confirms|accessdate=19 March 2020}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Singapore}}: Effective 20 March 2020, all arrivals from abroad will be issued Stay-Home Notices lasting 14 days.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Wong |first1=Lester |last2=Lim |first2=Min Zhang|title=Coronavirus: Record 47 new cases in S'pore; 14-day stay-home notice will apply to all returning residents and short-term visitors |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/covid-19-all-time-high-of-47-new-cases-in-singapore-14-day-stay-home-notice-will-now-apply |website=The Straits Times |accessdate=18 March 2020 |date=18 March 2020}}</ref>\n* {{flag|South Korea}}: Effective April 1, 2020, all passengers are subject to mandatory self-quarantine for 14 days. This does not apply to airline crew.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://restrictions.info/news/detail/3602 | title=Korea (Rep.) - restriction update 01.04.2020 02:52 UTC: COVID-19 Travel Restrictions Database}}</ref>\n\n==Non-global restrictions==\nMany countries have implemented measures that affect citizens of, or recent travelers to, a particular country or set of countries. Many of these countries later expanded their restrictions, with some later implementing global restrictions that may be listed above.\n\n[[File:COVID-19 Outbreak World Map-Travel Restrictions.svg|thumb|upright=1.81|Countries that have imposed travel restrictions related to China in response to the coronavirus pandemic as of 27 February 2020. These include countries that have enacted entry bans on Chinese citizens or recent visitors to China, halted issuing of visas to Chinese citizens or reimposed visa requirements on Chinese citizens, and countries that have responded with border closures with China.]]\n\n* {{flag|Angola}}: Visitors from China (People's Rep.), France, Iran, Italy, Korea (Rep.), Portugal or Spain are not allowed to enter or transit Angola. Citizens must be quarantined.<ref name=\"iatatravelcentre.com\">{{cite web|url=https://www.iatatravelcentre.com/international-travel-document-news/1580226297.htm|title=IATA - International Travel Document News|website=www.iatatravelcentre.com}}</ref> Arrivals from Japan denied entry.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.anzen.mofa.go.jp/covid19/pdfhistory_world.html|title=\u65b0\u578b\u30b3\u30ed\u30ca\u30a6\u30a4\u30eb\u30b9\uff08\u65e5\u672c\u304b\u3089\u306e\u6e21\u822a\u8005\u30fb\u65e5\u672c\u4eba\u306b\u5bfe\u3059\u308b\u5404\u56fd\u30fb\u5730\u57df\u306e\u5165\u56fd\u5236\u9650\u63aa\u7f6e\u53ca\u3073\u5165\u56fd\u5f8c\u306e\u884c\u52d5\u5236\u9650\uff09|last=\u5916\u52d9\u7701|first=|date=|website=\u5916\u52d9\u7701 \u6d77\u5916\u5b89\u5168\u30db\u30fc\u30e0\u30da\u30fc\u30b8|language=ja|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref>\n* {{flag|Antigua and Barbuda}}: Visitors who have travelled through Austria, Belgium, Bulgaria, Canada, 