sia, Netherlands, Norway, Qatar, Saudi Arabia, Spain, Sweden, Switzerland, United Kingdom or USA in the past 14 days will be quarantined for 14 days.<ref name=\"iatatravelcentre.com\"/>\n* {{flag|Fiji}}: Visitors from China (People's Rep.), Europe, Iran, Korea (Rep.) or USA are not allowed to enter or transit Fiji.<ref name=\"iatatravelcentre.com\"/>\n* {{flag|Gabon}}: Visitors who have travelled through Austria, Belgium, Bulgaria, China (People's Rep.), Croatia, Cyprus, Czechia, Denmark, Estonia, Finland, France, Germany, Greece, Hungary, Italy, Ireland (Rep.), Japan, Korea (Rep.), Latvia, Liechtenstein, Lithuania, Luxembourg, Malta, Netherlands, Norway, Poland, Portugal, Romania, Spain, Slovakia, Slovenia, Sweden, Switzerland, USA or the United Kingdom in the past 14 days are not allowed to enter or transit Gabon.<ref name=\"iatatravelcentre.com\"/><ref name=\":0\" />\n*{{flag|Germany}}: Effective March 16, 2020 Germany has partially closed its borders with France, Austria, Denmark, Luxembourg, and Switzerland. However, goods will continue to flow between the countries to curb panic-buying.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-51897069|title=Germany to impose border controls over coronavirus|date=March 15, 2020|via=BBC News}}</ref>\n* {{flag|Grenada}}: Visitors who have travelled through Austria, Belgium, Bulgaria, China (People's Rep.), Croatia, Cyprus, Czechia, Denmark, Estonia, Finland, France, Germany, Greece, Hungary, Iceland, Iran, Ireland (Rep.), Italy, Korea (Rep.), Latvia, Liechtenstein, Lithuania, Luxembourg, Malta, Netherlands, Norway, Poland, Portugal, Romania, Slovakia, Slovenia, Spain, Sweden, Switzerland, USA or the United Kingdom in the past 14 days are not allowed to enter Grenada.<ref name=\"iatatravelcentre.com\"/> Arrivals from Japan denied.<ref name=\":0\" />\n* {{flag|Guatemala}}: Banned arrivals from Canada and the United States starting mid-March.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-guatemala-idUSKBN211010|title=Guatemala bans arrivals from U.S., Canada to fight coronavirus|date=March 14, 2020|via=www.reuters.com}}</ref> Japanese nationals (except diplomats and those with residency permits) banned from entry.<ref name=\":0\" />\n* {{flag|Haiti}}: Visitors who have travelled through China (People's Rep.), France, Germany, Iran, Italy or Korea (Rep.) in the past 14 days are not allowed to enter or transit Haiti.<ref name=\"iatatravelcentre.com\"/> Visitors from Japan denied entry.<ref name=\":0\" />\n* {{flag|Hong Kong}}: Arrivals from the Schengen zone must be quarantined for 14 days starting from March 17.<ref>[https://www.scmp.com/news/hong-kong/health-environment/article/3075025/hong-kong-toddler-tests-positive-coronavirus Coronavirus: Hong Kong imposes quarantine restrictions on 26 European countries in Schengen zone] 13 March 2020, ''www.scmp.com'', accessed 15 March 2020</ref> Arrivals from Japan denied entry.<ref name=\":0\" />\n*{{flag|India}}: Issued a travel advisory on February 2, 2020 warning all people residing in India to not travel to China, suspended E-visas from China and stated that anyone who has travelled to China since 15 January (to an indefinite point in the future) could be quarantined.<ref name=\"twitter1224015130\"/> Has suspended all regular and e-visas issued on, or before, March 3, 2020 and banned travellers from South Korea from entering India through all ports of entry. People who need to travel to India, due to compelling reasons, need to apply for a fresh visa.<ref name=\"India Advisory\">{{cite web |title=Advisory: Travel and Visa restrictions related to COVID-19 |url=https://boi.gov.in/content/advisory-travel-and-visa-restrictions-related-covid-19 |website=Bureau of Immigration |publisher=Ministry of Home Affairs, Government of India |language=en}}</ref> Flights from Japan and e-visa issuance to Japanese nationals suspended.<ref name=\":0\" /> \n*{{flag|Indonesia}}: Announced on February 3, 2020 that it would ban passenger flights and sea freight from and to China starting on February 5 and until further notice. Live animal imports and other products were banned as well.<ref name=\"detik4884030\"/><ref name=\"AutoDW-166\"/><ref name=\"AutoDW-167\"/> An entry ban applies to visitors who travelled to [[Daegu]] and [[North Gyeongsang Province|Gyeongsangbuk]] within the past 14 days.<ref name=\"20200305indonesia\">{{cite news|url=https://www.straitstimes.com/asia/se-asia/coronavirus-indonesia-bans-entry-and-transit-of-foreigners-from-worst-stricken-regions|title=Coronavirus: Indonesia bans entry and transit of foreigners from worst-stricken regions in Iran, Italy and South Korea|date=5 March 2020|work=The Straits Times|accessdate=8 March 2020|language=en}}</ref> Visitors who have traveled from France, Germany, Iran, Italy, Spain, Switzerland, United Kingdom or Vatican City (Holy See) are not allowed to enter or transit Indonesia.<ref name=\":7\">{{cite web|url=https://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2020/03/17/covid-19-indonesia-suspends-visa-free-policy-expands-ban-for-people-from-worst-hit-countries.html|title=COVID-19: Indonesia suspends visa-free policy, expands ban for people from worst-hit countries|last=Post|first=The Jakarta|website=The Jakarta Post|language=en|access-date=2020-03-18}}</ref> Visitors from Japan not allowed entry.<ref name=\":0\" />\n* {{flag|Iraq}}: The government announced [[Basra International Airport]] would deny entry to passengers coming from China.<ref name=\"20200131reutersB\"/> Flights from Japan denied entry.<ref name=\":0\" />\n* {{flag|Israel}}: Initially banned citizens or visitors of [[Germany]], [[France]], [[Spain]], [[Switzerland]], [[Austria]], [[Andorra]] and [[San Marino]] unless they have proof that they have a place to self-quarantine for 14 days on March 6.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.timesofisrael.com/israel-begins-restrictions-on-visitors-from-5-european-nations-over-virus-fears/|title=Israel begins restrictions on visitors from 5 European nations over virus fears|date=2020-03-06|last=|first=|website=Times of Israel|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-03-07}}</ref> Entry ban from Japan and South Korea since February 23.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.japantimes.co.jp/news/2020/02/23/national/science-health/israel-south-korea-japan-flight-covid19/|title=Israel bans foreign visitors who traveled to Japan or South Korea as coronavirus fears surge|date=2020-02-23|work=The Japan Times Online|access-date=2020-04-02|language=en-US|issn=0447-5763}}</ref> On March 9, Israel instituted a blanket 14-day quarantine on all visitors and returning citizens.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.haaretz.com/israel-news/.premium-israeli-with-coronavirus-in-severe-condition-israel-may-quarantine-some-u-s-arrivals-1.8638322|title=Israel Extends Coronavirus Quarantine Orders to All Arrivals, 42 Cases Confirmed |date=2020-03-09|last=|first=|website=Haaretz|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-03-09}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Italy}}: Has suspended all passenger air traffic to Italy from mainland China, Hong Kong, Macau and Taiwan. The [[Italian Civil Aviation Authority]] [[NOTAM]] says that effective January 31, all passenger flights from China, including the [[special administrative regions of China|special administrative regions]] of Hong Kong and [[Macau]], as well as Taiwan, are suspended until further notice, on request of the Italian health authorities. Aircraft that were flying to Italy when the NOTAM was published were cleared to land.<ref name=\"Italy flights\"/><ref name=\"20200131enac\"/> Despite direct flights ban from/to China, Hong Kong, Macau and Taiwan, Chinese citizens with a Schengen Visa issued by another Schengen Country were allowed to enter Italy via flights with a stopover in other countries.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.corriere.it/cronache/20_gennaio_30/coronavirus-l-italia-ferma-voli-la-cina-ma-5-aerei-stanno-arrivando-roma-milano-4c159766-43a8-11ea-bdc8-faf1f56f19b7.shtml|title=Coronavirus, l'Italia ferma i voli con la Cina, gli ultimi aerei sono arrivati a Roma e Milano|language=it|date=30 January 2020|work= Corriere della Sera|first= Leonardo|last= Berbieri|access-date=March 25, 2020|trans-title=Italy stops flight from/to China, last flight have just landed at Rome and Milan airports}}</ref>\n* {{flag|Jamaica}}: Visitors who have travelled through China (People's Rep.), Chinese Taipei, France, Germany, Hong Kong (SAR China), Iran, Italy, Korea (Rep.), Macao (SAR China), Singapore, Spain or United Kingdom in the past 14 days are not allowed to enter or transit Jamaica.<ref name=\"iatatravelcentre.com\"/> Banned arrivals from Japan.<ref name=\":0\" />\n*{{flag|Japan}}: At the beginning of March, Japan revoked existing visas of people coming from China.<ref name=\":4\">{{cite web|url=https://www3.nhk.or.jp/nhkworld/en/news/20200306_23/|title=Japan's Cabinet approves visa cancellation policy {{!}} NHK WORLD-JAPAN News|website=NHK WORLD|language=en|access-date=2020-03-06}}</ref> From 3 April, foreign travellers present in the past 14 days in Europe (excluding Belarus, Russia and Ukraine) and select countries of Asia (Brunei, China, Hong Kong, Indonesia, Macau, Malaysia, Philippines, Republic of Korea, Singapore, Taiwan, Thailand, Vietnam), Oceania (Australia, New Zealand), North America (Canada, United States), Latin America (Bolivia, Brazil, Chile, Dominica, Ecuador, Panama), the Middle East (Bahrain, Iran, Israel, Turkey), and Africa (C\u00f4te d'Ivoire, Democratic Republic of the Congo, Egypt, Mauritius, Morocco) are barred from entry. Japanese citizens returning from those countries are required to undergo testing and potential quarantine.<ref>{{cite web |title=Coronavirus (COVID-19) advisory information {{!}} Travel Japan {{!}} JNTO |url=https://www.japan.travel/en/coronavirus/ |website=Japan National Tourism Organization (JNTO) |accessdate=7 April 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Kazakhstan}}: Suspended 72-hour visa-free transit for Chinese passengers.<ref name=\"AutoDW-156\"/> Arrivals from Japan banned.<ref name=\":0\" />\n*{{flag|Kiribati}}: Travellers who have been to a country with reported cases in the past 14 days prohibited from entering except with a medical certificate.<ref>{{cite news |title=UK travel advice: What countries have travel bans amid coronavirus outbreak? |url=https://metro.co.uk/2020/03/12/uk-travel-advice-countries-travel-bans-coronavirus-outbreak-12385713/ |accessdate=1 April 2020 |work=Metro |date=12 March 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Kuwait}}:<ref name=\"aa1719723\"/> Transport and visas [https://kuwaitvisa.com/travel-restrictions/ have been suspended between Kuwait and a number of countries], with nationals of certain sovereign states being temporarily banned from entering. Any traveler who has visited affected regions face similar restrictions.\n* {{flag|Macau}}: Entry denied to all travellers except residents of mainland China, Hong Kong, Macau, or Taiwan.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://macaunews.mo/macau-prohibits-non-residents-from-entering-macau-with-the-exception-of-those-from-mainland-china-hong-kong-and-taiwan/|title=Macau Prohibits Non-Residents from Entering Macau with the exception of those from Mainland China, Hong Kong and Taiwan|website=Macau News |accessdate=19 March 2020}}</ref> Previously, restrictions were implemented for travellers coming from a smaller set of countries.\n* {{flag|Maldives}}: Visitors who have travelled through Bangladesh, China (People's Rep.), Iran, Italy, Malaysia, Spain, Sri Lanka, United Kingdom or in North Gyeongsang and South Gyeongsang Provinces in Korea (Rep.), Ile-de-France and Grand Est (regions of France) and Bavaria, North Rhine Westphalia and Baden-Wuerttemberg (regions of Germany) in the past 14 days are not allowed to enter or transit Maldives.<ref name=\"iatatravelcentre.com\"/> Suspended visa issuance Japanese nationals, and banned tourist-related entries.<ref name=\":0\" />\n*{{flag|Micronesia}} has introduced a strict travel ban, banning anyone who had been in China anytime since January 2020 \u2014 or had been in any other affected country in the last 14 days \u2014 from entering Micronesia.<ref name=\"slate FSM\">{{cite web|url=https://slate.com/technology/2020/03/micronesia-drastic-coronavirus-travel-ban.html|title=The Most Drastic Anti-Coronavirus Travel Ban in the World|first=Rachel|last=Withers|date=March 5, 2020|website=Slate Magazine}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Nauru}}: Prohibited passengers who have been to Hong Kong, Iran, Italy, Japan, Macau, mainland China, or South Korea in the past 21 days.<ref name=\"iatatravelcentre.com\"/><ref name=\":0\" />\n*{{flag|New Zealand}}: Announced that it will deny entry to all travellers from China and that it will order its citizens to self-isolate for 14 days if they are returning from China.<ref name=\"WP\"/>\n* {{flag|Samoa}}: Visitors who have travelled through Australia, Austria, Bahrain, Belgium, Canada, China (People's Rep.), Chinese Taipei, Czechia, Denmark, France, Germany, Greece, Hong Kong (SAR China), Iceland, Italy, Iran, Japan, Korea (Rep.), Kuwait, Luxembourg, Macao (SAR China), Malaysia, Netherlands, Norway, Qatar, Singapore, Spain, Sweden, Switzerland, Thailand, United Arab Emirates or USA are not allowed to enter or transit Samoa.<ref name=\"iatatravelcentre.com\"/> Controversially, Samoa denied entry to several Samoan citizens, which was criticized as a violation of international law.<ref name=\"AutoDW-159\"/><ref name=\"AutoDW-160\"/>\n* {{flag|Singapore}}: Visitors who are from Germany, France, Spain and Italy are not allowed to enter or transit Singapore, and from March 16, 2020 at 11.59pm, it will be extended to all ASEAN countries, United Kingdom and Switzerland. Citizens must be quarantined for 14 days.<ref name=\"20200303mohsg\" /><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/singapore-residents-advised-to-defer-all-non-essential-travel-for-next-30-days-as-part-of|title=Singaporeans advised to defer all non-essential travel for next 30 days, as part of new Covid-19 measures|date=March 15, 2020|website=The Straits Times}}</ref> Entries from Japan (including transits) not allowed, except for those with permanent residence permits.<ref name=\":0\" />\n*{{flag|Somalia}}: banned passengers who had been to China, Iran, South Korea, or Italy in the past 14 days.<ref name=\"Somalia bans entry\">{{cite news |title=COVID-19: Somalia bans entry from worst-hit countries |url=https://www.aa.com.tr/en/latest-on-coronavirus-outbreak/covid-19-somalia-bans-entry-from-worst-hit-countries/1766837 |accessdate=22 March 2020 |work=www.aa.com.tr}}</ref> Banned flights from Japan.<ref name=\":0\" />\n* {{flag|South Africa}}: Visitors from China (People's Rep.), France, Germany, Iran, Italy, Japan, Korea (Rep.), Spain, Switzerland, USA or United Kingdom are not allowed to enter or transit South Africa.<ref name=\"iatatravelcentre.com\"/><ref name=\":0\" />\n*{{flag|Taiwan}}: Prohibited entry to Chinese nationals and foreign nationals who have travelled to mainland China, Hong Kong, or Macau in the past 14 days.<ref name=\"TWCDC06Feb2020\"/> Entry from Japan denied.<ref name=\":0\" />\n*{{flag|Trinidad and Tobago}}: Health Minister [[Ter\u00adrance Deyals\u00adingh]] announced that [[Trinidad and Tobago]] had decided to implement restrictions on persons traveling from [[China]]. Persons who are living or who have visited China, will be barred from entering Trinidad and Tobago unless they had already been out of China 14 days prior to attempting to travel to Trinidad & Tobago.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.looptt.com/content/covid-19-tt-closes-borders-non-nationals-14-days |title = COVID-19: T&T closes borders to non-nationals for 14 days}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.caribbean360.com/news/trinidad-tobago-shuts-out-international-community-for-two-weeks-to-stem-spread-of-covid-19 |title = Trinidad & Tobago Shuts Out International Community to Stem Spread of COVID-19; Schools Closed|date = 16 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"TT Cabinet announces 14-day travel restrictions\">{{cite web |url=http://www.guardian.co.tt/neo/NeoProxy.dll?app=NeoDirect&com=6/2/1042978/7a4c342a7f |title=Cabinet announces 14-day travel restrictions from China |website=guardian.co.tt |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200222113407/https://www.guardian.co.tt/neo/NeoProxy.dll?app=NeoDirect&com=6%2F2%2F1042978%2F7a4c342a7f |archive-date=22 February 2020 |access-date=27 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.guardian.co.tt/news/3-more-european-nations-on-tts-covidrestricted-list-6.2.1076451.75af2508a7 | title=3 more European nations on T&T's COVID-restricted list}}</ref> Travellers whose flights originate from&nbsp;Italy, South Korea, Singapore, Japan, Iran, Germany, Spain, and France are also to be restricted.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.guardian.co.tt/news/3-more-european-nations-on-tts-covidrestricted-list-6.2.1076451.75af2508a7 |title = 3 more European nations on T&T's COVID-restricted list}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Turkey}}: announced it would suspend all flights from China till the end of February and begin scanning passengers coming from Japan, Taiwan, Hong Kong, Singapore, South Korea, and Malaysia at airports.<ref name=\"gazeteduvar\"/><ref name=\"aa1722860\"/> All Iranian nationals are banned from entering Turkey. Passengers who have transited through or have been in Iran in the past 14 days are not allowed to transit or enter Turkey. Also suspended the incoming flights from Iran on February 23, 2020,<ref name=\"Hurriyet\">{{cite news |title=9 Avrupa \u00fclkesine u\u00e7u\u015f yasa\u011f\u0131 |url=https://www.hurriyet.com.tr/gundem/son-dakika-haberi-9-avrupa-ulkesine-ucus-yasagi-41468591 |accessdate=13 March 2020 |work=H\u00fcrriyet |date=13 March 2020 |language=tr}}</ref> Nationals of Austria, Belgium, Denmark, France, Germany, the Netherlands, Norway, Spain and Sweden are not allowed to enter Turkey. Passengers who have transited through or have been in Austria, Belgium, Denmark, France, Germany, the Netherlands, Norway, Spain and Sweden in the past 14 days are not allowed to transit or enter Turkey. Also suspended the incoming flights from these countries effective from March 14, 2020. This restriction does not apply to nationals of Turkey and residents of Turkey.<ref name=\"iatatravelcentre.com\"/> Tourists arriving from these locations will not be allowed to pass through national immigration even if they have a valid eVisa or another form of travel authorization. Foreign visitors who have been in these nations up to [https://www.visasturkey.com/travel-and-entry-restrictions/ 14 days prior to arriving in Turkey] will also face restrictions and barriers to entry. Flights from Japan not allowed entry.<ref name=\":0\" />\n*{{flag|United States}}: On January 31, 2020, the United States declared the virus a [[Public health emergency (United States)|public health emergency]]. Starting February 2, all inbound passengers who have been to Hubei in the previous 14 days will be put under quarantine for up to 14 days. American citizens who have travelled to the rest of mainland China will be allowed to continue their travel home if they are asymptomatic, but will be monitored by local health departments.<ref name=\"nbcnews1127856\"/> As of March 2, foreign nationals who have travelled to Iran within the past 14 days are denied permission to enter the US.<ref name=\"2020-03-02cnn\"/> American citizens and permanent residents returning to the United States who have travelled to Iran within the previous 14 days must enter through an approved airport.<ref name=\"2020-03-02cnn\"/><ref name=\"iatatravelcentre.com\"/> Suspended incoming travel from the [[Schengen area]] in Europe, beginning at 23:59 [[Eastern Time Zone|ET]] on March 13.<ref name=EUban>{{cite web|url=https://www.whitehouse.gov/presidential-actions/proclamation-suspension-entry-immigrants-nonimmigrants-certain-additional-persons-pose-risk-transmitting-2019-novel-coronavirus/|title=Proclamation\u2014Suspension of Entry as Immigrants and Nonimmigrants of Certain Additional Persons Who Pose a Risk of Transmitting 2019 Novel Coronavirus|date=2020-03-11|website=The White House|first=Donald|last=Trump}}</ref> The official proclamation states that this restriction applies only to foreign nationals traveling to the United States, if they have been to a country within the [[Schengen area]] in the past 14 days. The ban does not apply to for example legal permanent residents and most immediate family members of U.S. citizens.<ref name=EUban/> Also, cargo and trading goods are not affected.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dw.com/en/coronavirus-latest-trump-suspends-travel-from-europes-schengen-countries/a-52731894|title=Coronavirus latest: Trump suspends travel from Europe's Schengen countries|website=Deutsche Welle|language=en-GB|access-date=2020-03-12}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-51846923|title=Trump halts travel from Europe to US|date=2020-03-12|work=BBC News|access-date=2020-03-12|language=en-GB}}</ref> On March 14, Trump administration extended the ban to include United Kingdom and Ireland.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.foxnews.com/politics/trump-european-travel-ban-uk-ireland|title=Trump administration to extend European travel ban to include UK and Ireland|last=Shaw|first=Adam|date=2020-03-14|website=Fox News|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-14}}</ref> The restrictions will reportedly be in place for 30 days,<ref>{{Cite news|last=Specia|first=Megan|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/03/12/world/europe/trump-travel-ban-coronavirus.html|title=What You Need to Know About Trump's European Travel Ban|date=2020-03-12|work=The New York Times|access-date=2020-03-15|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref> however the official proclamation does not contain that time limit, stating; \"This proclamation shall remain in effect until terminated by the President.\"<ref name=\"EUban\" />\n* {{flag|Uruguay}}: Visitors from Argentina, China (People's Rep.), France, Germany, Iran, Italy, Japan, Korea (Rep.), Singapore or Spain are not allowed to enter or transit Uruguay.<ref name=\"iatatravelcentre.com\"/>\n* {{flag|Vietnam}}: Suspended visa issuance for Chinese tourists.<ref name=\"20200130reuters\"/> Suspended the visa waiver for citizens of Denmark, Finland, France, Germany, Norway, Spain, Sweden and United Kingdom effective from March 12, 2020,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mofa.gov.vn/en/nr040807104143/nr040807105001/ns200311161021|title=Temporary suspension of unilateral visa waiver to European countries regarding the COVID-19 situation|publisher=[[Ministry of Foreign Affairs (Vietnam)|Vietnam MFA]]}}</ref> and for Italy from March 3.<ref name=\"vietnam-mfa-updates\">{{cite web|url=http://www.mofa.gov.vn/en/tt_baochi/pbnfn/ns200312141207|title=Updated information on COVID-19 pandemic|publisher=[[Ministry of Foreign Affairs (Vietnam)|Vietnam MFA]]}}</ref> Entry from Japan denied.<ref name=\":0\" /> Embassies and travel agencies have also been instructed not to issue regular visas to citizens from the above countries, for the time being.  Vietnam has announced that from 12:00 (UTC+07:00) on March 15, 2020 all foreign nationals will be refused entry to Vietnam if in the previous 14 days they have been to the UK, or any Schengen country, even in transit. This restriction will be in place for 30 days.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gov.uk/foreign-travel-advice/vietnam?utm_source=c37d8398-0338-4191-a8d3-82f8a146a447&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=govuk-notifications&utm_content=immediate|title=Vietnam: Foreign travel advice|website=Gov.uk|accessdate=March 15, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mofa.gov.vn/en/nr040807104143/nr040807105001/ns200314083802|title=Temporary regulatory change on entry, exit for foreigners|publisher=[[Ministry of Foreign Affairs (Vietnam)|Vietnam MFA]]}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n