ag|El Salvador}}: On March 11, the President of El Salvador announced an Executive Order barring the entry of foreigners.<ref name=\"elsalvador.1\">{{cite web|url=https://sv.usembassy.gov/health-alert-u-s-embassy-san-salvador-el-salvador-march-12-2020/|title=Health Alert \u2013 U.S. Embassy San Salvador, El Salvador &#124; U.S. Embassy in El Salvador|date=March 12, 2020|website=U.S. Embassy in \u00a0 El\u00a0Salvador}}</ref> The General Directorate of Migration will deny entry to all foreigners, excluding accredited diplomats and legal residents of El Salvador.<ref name=\"elsalvador.1\" />\n*{{flag|Guatemala}}: The Guatemalan Government announced on March 16 that the country was closing its borders for two weeks, starting on midnight March 17.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/article/coronavirus-travel-restrictions.html|title=Coronavirus Travel Restrictions, Across the Globe|website=The New York Times|accessdate=March 17, 2020}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Guyana}}: Airports in Guyana are closed to all international passenger flights until 1 May 2020.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://restrictions.info/news/detail/3893 | title=Guyana - restriction update 04.04.2020 11:22 UTC: COVID-19 Travel Restrictions Database}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Honduras}}: Borders closed to all traffic, aside from the movement of goods, effective March 15, 23:59.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://hn.usembassy.gov/covid-19-information/|title=COVID-19 Information|date=March 26, 2020|website=U.S. Embassy in Honduras}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Jamaica}}: No entry except by government authorization.<ref name=\"iatatravelcentre.com\"/>\n*{{flag|Panama}}: From 11.59 p.m on Monday night (March 16), only Panamanians and foreign residents would be allowed to enter Panama.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.garda.com/crisis24/news-alerts/323071/panama-authorities-prohibit-all-foreigners-from-entering-the-country-due-to-covid-19-march-16-update-3 |title=Panama: Authorities prohibit all foreigners from entering the country due to COVID-19 March 16 /update 3 |publisher=Garda.com |date=2020-03-16 |accessdate=2020-03-30}}</ref> From 11.59 pm on Sunday 22 March, all international flights will be halted.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gov.uk/foreign-travel-advice/panama/coronavirus|title=Foreign travel advice: Panama|last=|first=|date=2020|website=gov.uk|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=March 26, 2020}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Paraguay}}: Flights to Paraguay are suspended until 12 April 2020.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://restrictions.info/tr/country/py/ | title=Travel restrictions of Paraguay: COVID-19 Travel Restrictions Database}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=https://restrictions.info/news/detail/3226 | title=Travel restrictions update for Paraguay - 25.03.2020: COVID-19 Travel Restrictions Database}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Peru}}: Peru restricts access to the interior of the country from 12:00 on March 17.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://gestion.pe/peru/coronavirus-en-peru-presidente-martin-vizcarra-anuncia-cierre-de-todas-las-fronteras-durante-estado-de-emergencia-nndc-noticia/|title=Per\u00fa anuncia el cierre de todas sus fronteras para evitar el avance de coronavirus: Vigente desde el martes|first=Redacci\u00f3n|last=Gesti\u00f3n|date=March 16, 2020|website=Gesti\u00f3n}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Suriname}}: Will close its borders for all persons and flights starting March 14.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-suriname-confirmed/suriname-confirms-first-coronavirus-case-authorities-will-close-borders-idUSKBN210373 |title=Suriname confirms first coronavirus case, authorities will close borders |date=13 March 2020 |work=Reuters |access-date=13 March 2020 |via=www.reuters.com}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Trinidad and Tobago}}: On March 16, Trinidad and Tobago announced that it closed its borders to all except Trinidad and Tobago nationals and certain medical personnel,<ref>{{Cite news|last=Nanton|first=Sampson|url=http://www.guardian.co.tt/news/tt-shuts-down-borders-bars-to-be-closed-6.2.1080079.6b07bec899|title=T&T shuts down borders, bars to be closed|date=2020-03-16|work=Trinidad and Tobago Guardian|access-date=2020-03-16|url-status=live}}</ref> by midnight on March 17.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Clyne|first=Kalifa Sarah|url=https://newsday.co.tt/2020/03/16/government-shuts-tt-borders/|title=Government shuts TT borders|date=2020-03-16|work=Trinidad and Tobago Newsday|access-date=2020-03-16|url-status=live}}</ref> Airports in Trinidad and Tobago are closed until 30 April 2020.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://restrictions.info/news/detail/3541 | title=Trinidad and Tobago - restriction update 30.03.2020 09:18 UTC: COVID-19 Travel Restrictions Database}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Uruguay}}<ref>{{cite news |title=Cierre total de fronteras para extranjeros, salvo en ciudades de frontera con Brasil |url=https://www.subrayado.com.uy/uruguay-resuelve-el-cierre-absoluto-fronteras-extranjeros-ciudades-fronterizas-brasil-n614022 |accessdate=5 April 2020 |work=subrayado.com.uy |language=es-ES}}</ref>\n\n=== Europe ===\n* {{flag|European Union}}: The European Council agreed on March 17 to ban incoming travel other than citizens from countries in the [[European Union]], [[European Economic Area]], Switzerland and United Kingdom, [[Long-term resident (European Union)|long-term residents]] and people with long-term visa or residence permits, family members of EU and EEA citizens, medical personnel and people responsible for transport of goods for 30 days.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.consilium.europa.eu/en/meetings/european-council/2020/03/17/ |title = Video conference of the members of the European Council, 17 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.politico.eu/article/the-eu-european-union-coronavirus-covid19-travel-ban-explained/ |title = The EU travel ban explained|date = 17 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.europapress.es/internacional/noticia-lideres-europeos-aceptan-cerrar-fronteras-exteriores-ue-viajes-esenciales-20200317203959.html|title=Los l\u00edderes europeos aceptan cerrar las fronteras exteriores de la UE salvo para viajes \"esenciales\"|first=Europa|last=Press|date=March 17, 2020|website=www.europapress.es}}</ref> Each country has to implement the decision on the national level. Ireland choose to opt out from the decision due to the [[Common Travel Area]]. The agreement was to close borders for 30 days starting at noon on March 17, though enforcement did not begin immediately as planned.<ref>[https://www.schengenvisainfo.com/news/breaking-eu-decides-to-close-all-schengen-borders-for-30-days/ BREAKING: EU Decides to Close All Schengen Borders For 30 Days]</ref> By the end of March, all EU member states (except Ireland) and all associated Schengen states (Iceland, Liechtenstein, Norway and Switzerland) had introduced the travel restriction.<ref>[https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/PDF/?uri=CELEX:52020XC0330(02)]</ref> Some member states choose to go further and also prohibited EU and EEA citizens from entering, unless they are permanently living in the country or transiting to their home country.\n*{{flag|Austria}}: Closed borders for persons not having medical certificate confirming negative test for SARS-CoV-2, not older than four days upon entry.<ref>{{cite web |title=Grenzkontrollma\u00dfnahmen an \u00d6sterreichs Grenzen |url=https://bmi.gv.at/news.aspx?id=314A5A707A4547684D55733D |website=bmi.gv.at |accessdate=2 April 2020 |language=de}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Belgium}}: Closed its borders to non-essential travel on March 20.<ref>{{cite web |title=Belgian borders shut to non-essential travel |url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/world/belgian-borders-shut-to-non-essential-travel-12562392 |website=CNA |accessdate=2 April 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Croatia}}: Closed its borders to non-citizens on March 19.<ref>{{cite web |title=Croatia imposes new restrictions concerning cross-border traffic |url=https://www.croatiaweek.com/croatia-imposes-new-restrictions-concerning-cross-border-traffic/ |website=Croatia Week |accessdate=5 April 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Czech Republic}}: Partially closed its borders on March 14. Closed its borders to all non-residents on March 16.<ref name=\"czech.1\">{{cite web|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=2020_coronavirus_pandemic_in_the_Czech_Republic&oldid=945894827|title=2020 coronavirus pandemic in the Czech Republic|date=March 16, 2020|via=Wikipedia}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Denmark}}: Closed its borders to all non-citizens March 14.<ref name=\"denmark.1\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/health-coronavirus-denmark-idUSL8N2B673O|title=Denmark shutting its borders to curb spread of coronavirus, prime minister says|newspaper=Reuters|date=March 13, 2020|via=www.reuters.com}}</ref>  This includes a ban on crossing the border for all tourism, but exempts travellers with \"credible purpose\" such as non-citizen Danish residents.<ref name=\"denmark.1\" />\n*{{flag|Estonia}}: Effective March 17, 2020, foreign travelers are not allowed to enter. Right of entry will remain for citizens and those with a right of residence, and foreign citizens whose next of kin live in Estonia. Transit is allowed for foreigners not showing signs of the coronavirus. A mandatory two-week quarantine will be set for anyone entering the country.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.err.ee/1064173/estonia-to-close-borders-to-foreign-nationals-from-march-17|title=Estonia to close borders to foreign nationals from March 17|date=March 15, 2020|website=ERR}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Finland}}: Closed its borders on March 19, 2020, except for Finnish citizens returning to Finland, foreigners returning to their countries of origin, essential work-related travel, and goods. Finnish citizens returning home are recommended to quarantine themselves for 14 days after arrival.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://yle.fi/uutiset/3-11262175|title=Muutokset astuvat voimaan: Koronaviruksen aiheuttama poikkeustila sulkee koulut t\u00e4n\u00e4\u00e4n, rajat kiinni torstaina|date=March 18, 2020|website=Yle|access-date=March 20, 2020|language=fi}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Hungary}}: Hungary closed its borders for all passenger transport on March 17 and only Hungarian citizens and permanent residents are allowed to enter.<ref>{{cite web |title=Borders Closed: Who Can Enter Hungary and How? |url=https://hungarytoday.hu/borders-closed-who-can-enter-hungary-and-how/ |website=Hungary Today |accessdate=5 April 2020 |language=en |date=17 March 2020}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Latvia}}: Effective March 17, 2020 all international passenger connections by air, railway, sea and road, were be cancelled. Only Latvians and foreigners with residency rights in Latvia will be able to enter the country from outside the Schengen Area,<ref>{{cite web |title=Emergency situation in Latvia to restrict the spread of Covid-19 |url=https://www.mfa.gov.lv/en/consular-information/news/65754-emergency-situation-declared-throughout-the-national-territory-until-14-april-2020-to-restrict-the-spread-of-covid-19 |website=Ministry of Foreign Affairs of the Republic of Latvia |accessdate=27 March 2020 |date=17 March 2020}}</ref> but entry of foreign citizens by private vehicle from other Schengen member countries was still allowed.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://eng.lsm.lv/article/society/health/latvia-to-close-borders-to-passenger-traffic-on-tuesday-17-march.a351774/|title=Latvia to close borders to passenger traffic on Tuesday 17 March|date=2020-03-14|work=LSM.LV|access-date=2020-03-26|language=en}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Lithuania}}: Closed the border for foreigners, except for those with residence permits, effective 00:00 (UTC+02:00) March 16 \u2013 April 13, 2020.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://lrv.lt/lt/naujienos/vyriausybe-nusprende-karantinas-tesiamas-iki-balandzio-13-dienos|title=Vyriausyb\u0117 nusprend\u0117: karantinas t\u0119siamas iki baland\u017eio 13 dienos|date=2020-03-25}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Norway}}: Effective March 16, 2020, closed airports temporarily. Foreigners are turned away, and exemptions are made for Norwegians returning from abroad, and for goods.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://uk.reuters.com/article/uk-health-coronavirus-norway-airport-idUKKBN2110Z0|title=Norway to close ports, airports from Monday to stop coronavirus - PM|date=2020-03-14|work=Reuters|access-date=2020-03-15|language=en}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Moldova}}: Closed its airspace and terrestrial borders for all foreigners, except for diplomats and permanent residents, effective from 00:00 (UTC+02:00) March 17, 2020.<ref>[https://tass.ru/obschestvo/7984033 \u041c\u043e\u043b\u0434\u0430\u0432\u0438\u044f \u0437\u0430\u043a\u0440\u044b\u0432\u0430\u0435\u0442 \u0433\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0446\u0443 \u0438\u0437-\u0437\u0430 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0430 \u0441 17 \u043c\u0430\u0440\u0442\u0430]. tass.ru (15 March 2020)</ref>\n*{{flag|Poland}}: Effective March 15 \u2013 April 11, 2020, entry ban for all foreigners except for those with residential or work permits, and 14 days' quarantine on all people entering.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-poland-foreigners-idUSKBN21031F|title=Poland to close borders to foreigners, quarantine returnees|newspaper=Reuters|date=March 13, 2020|via=www.reuters.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gov.pl/web/koronawirus/zamykamy-granice-przed-koronawirusem|title=Zamykamy granice przed koronawirusem|date=2020-03-13|via =www.Gov.pl}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gov.pl/web/koronawirus/pytania-i-odpowiedzi|title=Najcz\u0119\u015bciej zadawane pytania|via =www.Gov.pl}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Romania}}: Effective March 22, 2020 Romania banned foreign citizens from entering the country with the exception of official residents or those who are transiting the country.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.romania-insider.com/coronavirus-romania-borders-malls-closed|title=Coronavirus in Romania: Country closes borders for foreign citizens, malls close, people's movement and religious service restricted|website=Romania Insider|language=en|access-date=2020-03-25}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Russia}}: Borders closed to foreigners with some exceptions, effective March 18 and until May 1.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/coronavirus-russia-border-close-flights-when-residents-latest-a9405131.html|title=Russia closes borders until May amid coronavirus pandemic|date=March 16, 2020|website=The Independent}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Serbia}}: Closed its borders on March 16.<ref>{{cite web |title=Serbia closes its borders to foreigners over coronavirus |url=https://www.euractiv.com/section/justice-home-affairs/news/serbia-closes-its-borders-to-foreigners-over-coronavirus/ |website=www.euractiv.com |accessdate=3 April 2020 |date=16 March 2020}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Slovakia}}: Closed its borders to all nonresidents on March 13.<ref name=\"slovakia.1\">[https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2020-03-12/slovakia-closes-borders-for-non-residents-to-fight-coronavirus Bloomberg - Are you a robot?<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>  Closed international airports and require all residents returning from abroad to quarantine.<ref name=\"slovakia.1\" />  Violators may be fined up to 1659 EUR.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uvzsr.sk/index.php?view=article&id=4087|title=COVID-19: \u00dastredn\u00fd kr\u00edzov\u00fd \u0161t\u00e1b zav\u00e1dza \u010fal\u0161ie opatrenia, zatvoria sa \u0161koly i\u00a0letisk\u00e1, karant\u00e9na plat\u00ed pre v\u0161etk\u00fdch, ktor\u00ed sa vr\u00e1tia zo zahrani\u010dia|website=www.uvzsr.sk}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Spain}}: Closed borders to non-residents on March 17.<ref>{{cite web |title=Spain closes its borders to contain spread of coronavirus |url=https://english.elpais.com/society/2020-03-16/spain-closes-its-borders-to-contain-coronavirus.html |website=EL PA\u00cdS |accessdate=3 April 2020 |language=en |date=16 March 2020}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Switzerland}}: Borders closed to foreigners, starting 17 March 2020.\n*{{flag|Turkey}}: Effective March 28, Turkey is suspending all international flights to and from Turkey, amid [[COVID-19]] outbreak. Turkey also closed its borders with all its neighbours.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.aa.com.tr/en/latest-on-coronavirus-outbreak/turkey-cancels-all-int-l-flights-amid-covid-19-outbreak/1782602|title=Turkey cancels all int\u2019l flights amid COVID-19 outbreak|date=March 27, 2020|website=Anadolu Agency}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.aa.com.tr/en/turkey/turkey-closes-border-gates-with-greece-bulgaria/1770793|title=Turkey closes border gates with Greece, Bulgaria|date=March 27, 2020|website=Anadolu Agency}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Ukraine}}: Starting March 15, Ukraine has closed its border for foreigners for two weeks. Returning Ukrainian citizens will be required to submit to health observation procedures.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://112.international/ukraine-top-news/ukraine-closing-border-for-foreigners-for-two-weeks-49475.html|title=Ukraine closing border for foreigners for two weeks|website=112.international}}</ref> Effective March 17, Ukraine is suspending all commercial passenger services, including flights, trains and passenger buses, to and from Ukraine for a period of two weeks.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ua.usembassy.gov/covid-19-information/|title=COVID-19 Information|date=March 13, 2020|website=U.S. Embassy in Ukraine}}</ref>\n\n===Oceania===\n* {{flag|Australia}}: Borders closed to all non-citizens or permanent residents from 21:00 March 20.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.abc.net.au/news/2020-03-19/coronavirus-non-resident-travel-ban-australia/12071640|title=Australia blocks arrival of all non-residents in expanded coronavirus travel ban|accessdate=March 19, 2020}}</ref>\n* {{flag|Marshall Islands}}: Passengers are not allowed to enter Marshall Isl. until 5 May 2020.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://restrictions.info/tr/country/mh/ | title=Travel restrictions of Marshall Islands: COVID-19 Travel Restrictions Database}}</ref>\n* {{flag|New Caledonia}}: Passengers except parents of a French minor and spouses of a national of France are not allowed to enter New Caledonia. Flights to New Caledonia are suspended until 31 May 2020.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://restrictions.info/news/detail/3605 | title=Travel restrictions of Vanuatu: COVID-19 Travel Restrictions Database}}</ref>\n* {{flag|New Zealand}}: Borders closed to all non-citizens or permanent residents including the previously exempt Pacific Islands or temporary visa holders (such as students) from 23:59 March 19.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.rnz.co.nz/news/national/412162/nz-to-close-its-borders-to-anyone-not-a-citizen-or-permanent-resident-pm-confirms|title=NZ to close its borders to anyone not a citizen or permanent resident., PM confirms|accessdate=March 19, 2020}}</ref>\n* {{flag|Fiji}}: Borders closed to all non-citizens.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.itij.com/latest/news/fiji-airways-suspends-95-cent-its-international-flights|title=Fiji closes borders|accessdate=March 22, 2020}}</ref>\n* {{flag|Tuvalu}}: Tuvalu's borders are closed.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://restrictions.info/tr/country/tv/ | title=Travel restrictions of Tuvalu: COVID-19 Travel Restrictions Database}}</ref>\n* {{flag|Vanuatu}}: Vanuatu ports of entry are closed from 20 March 2020.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://restrictions.info/tr/country/vu/ | title=Travel restrictions of Vanuatu: COVID-19 Travel Restrictions Database}}</ref>\n\n==Countries implementing global quarantine measures ==\n* {{flag|Australia}}: The Australian Government has announced that any person \u2013 regardless of citizenship or residency status \u2013 travelling to Australia from any international destination will be required to undergo a compulsory 14-day quarantine, beginning from their date of arrival. The regulations, effective from March 16, 2020, also ban cruise ships arriving from international waters from docking at any Australian port.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Wright |first1=Shane |title=PM introduces strict travel restrictions for all arrivals |url=https://www.smh.com.au/national/pm-introduces-strict-travel-restrictions-for-all-arrivals-20200315-p54a8q.html |work=The Sydney Morning Herald |date=15 March 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n* {{flag|Benin}}: 14-day quarantine.<ref name=\"iatatravelcentre.com\"/>\n*{{flag|Canada}}: Effective midnight March 25, 2020, the Canadian government announced an Emergency Order under the ''[[Quarantine Act, 2005|Quarantine Act]]'' that requires any person entering Canada by air, sea or land to self-isolate for 14 days whether or not they have symptoms of COVID-19.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.canada.ca/en/public-health/news/2020/03/new-order-makes-self-isolation-mandatory-for-individuals-entering-canada.html|title=New Order Makes Self-Isolation Mandatory for Individuals Entering Canada|date=March 25, 2020|website=Government of Canada}}</ref>\n* {{flag|Chile}}: Will not permit cruise ships to dock as of March 15. Travelers who have been to countries of concern are subject to examination or quarantine upon arrival.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://cl.usembassy.gov/covid-19-information/|title=COVID-19 in Chile: Information for American Citizens|date=March 5, 2020|website=U.S. Embassy in Chile}}</ref>\n* {{flag|Ethiopia}}: Mandatory 14-day quarantine at the traveller's expense.<ref name=\"iatatravelcentre.com\"/>\n* {{flag|Fiji}}: After the lockdown of [[Lautoka]] on 20 March 2020, no person regardless of citizenship is allowed to leave the confines of the city.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fbcnews.com.fj/news/covid-19/pm-no-exceptions-to-leave-lautoka-during-lockdown/|title=No exceptions to leave Lautoka|date=March 22, 2020|website=FBC}}</ref>\n* {{flag|Guernsey}}: Imposed a requirement on all persons arriving in the Bailiwick from anywhere in the world (including Jersey and the UK) to self-isolate for 14 days on arrival. This is a legal requirement, and failure to comply is a criminal offence.<ref>[https://gov.gg/CHttpHandler.ashx?id=124043&p=0] 19 March 2020 \"www.gov.gg\", accessed 20 March 2020</ref>\n*{{flag|Hong Kong}}: Effective 19 March 2020, all persons arriving in Hong Kong who have been to Mainland China or any overseas countries/territories (excluding [[Macao]] and [[Taiwan]]) in the past 14 days, regardless of whether they are Hong Kong residents, are subject to compulsory quarantine.<ref>{{cite web |title=COVID-19 Thematic Website - Together, We Fight the Virus - Inbound Travel |url=https://www.coronavirus.gov.hk/eng/inbound-travel.html |publisher=Hong Kong SAR Government |accessdate=19 March 2020}}</ref> Effective 25 March 2020, all persons arriving in Hong Kong, regardless of whether they are Hong Kong residents, are subject to compulsory quarantine.<ref>{{cite web |title=HK to turn away many non-residents for 14 days |url=https://news.rthk.hk/rthk/en/component/k2/1516270-20200323.htm |publisher=RTHK |accessdate=23 March 2020}}</ref> \n* {{flag|Jersey}}: From Friday 20 March, all travellers arriving in Jersey must now self-isolate for 14 days. This includes the UK, Guernsey, Europe and the rest of the world.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gov.je/Health/Coronavirus/Pages/CoronavirusTravelAdvice.aspx |title=Travel advice for coronavirus (COVID-19) |publisher=Gov.je |date= |accessdate=2020-03-30}}</ref>\n* {{flag|Malta}}: Tourists entering Malta from any country from 13:30 on March 13, 2020 onwards must spend 14 days in mandatory quarantine, which 14 days start from the last day that they were in any of these countries. This is enforceable by law. Failure to observe this obligation will result in fines of \u20ac1,000 for each time it is breached.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.visitmalta.com/en/Covid-19|title=Visitmalta - The official tourism website for Malta, Gozo and Comino.|website=www.visitmalta.com}}</ref>\n* {{flag|New Zealand}}: Beginning March 15, any person travelling into New Zealand from overseas, including New Zealand citizens, will be required to self-isolate for 14 days following entry into the country, except for those travelling from the Pacific Islands unless they are displaying symptoms. All cruise ships have been banned entry into New Zealand until June 30.<ref name=\"tvnz15032020\">{{cite news|title=Everyone entering New Zealand will be required to isolate, cruise ships banned|url=https://www.tvnz.co.nz/one-news/new-zealand/covid-19-everyone-entering-new-zealand-required-isolate-cruise-ships-banned|accessdate=15 March 2020}}</ref> Beginning 23:59 on March 19, New Zealand will not permit any new arrivals to non-citizens or permanent residents including the previously excluded Pacific Islands and temporary visa holders.<ref>{{cite news|title=NZ to close its borders to anyone not a citizen or permanent resident., PM confirms|url=https://www.rnz.co.nz/news/national/412162/live-nz-to-close-its-borders-to-anyone-not-a-citizen-or-permanent-resident-pm-confirms|accessdate=19 March 2020}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Singapore}}: Effective 20 March 2020, all arrivals from abroad will be issued Stay-Home Notices lasting 14 days.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Wong |first1=Lester |last2=Lim |first2=Min Zhang|title=Coronavirus: Record 47 new cases in S'pore; 14-day stay-home notice will apply to all returning residents and short-term visitors |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/covid-19-all-time-high-of-47-new-cases-in-singapore-14-day-stay-home-notice-will-now-apply |website=The Straits Times |accessdate=18 March 2020 |date=18 March 2020}}</ref>\n* {{flag|South Korea}}: Effective April 1, 2020, all passengers are subject to mandatory self-quarantine for 14 days. This does not apply to airline crew.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://restrictions.info/news/detail/3602 | title=Korea (Rep.) - restriction update 01.04.2020 02:52 UTC: COVID-19 Travel Restrictions Database}}</ref>\n\n==Non-global restrictions==\nMany countries have implemented measures that affect citizens of, or recent travelers to, a particular country or set of countries. Many of these countries later expanded their restrictions, with some later implementing global restrictions that may be listed above.\n\n[[File:COVID-19 Outbreak World Map-Travel Restrictions.svg|thumb|upright=1.81|Countries that have imposed travel restrictions related to China in response to the coronavirus pandemic as of 27 February 2020. These include countries that have enacted entry bans on Chinese citizens or recent visitors to China, halted issuing of visas to Chinese citizens or reimposed visa requirements on Chinese citizens, and countries that have responded with border closures with China.]]\n\n* {{flag|Angola}}: Visitors from China (People's Rep.), France, Iran, Italy, Korea (Rep.), Portugal or Spain are not allowed to enter or transit Angola. Citizens must be quarantined.<ref name=\"iatatravelcentre.com\">{{cite web|url=https://www.iatatravelcentre.com/international-travel-document-news/1580226297.htm|title=IATA - International Travel Document News|website=www.iatatravelcentre.com}}</ref> Arrivals from Japan denied entry.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.anzen.mofa.go.jp/covid19/pdfhistory_world.html|title=\u65b0\u578b\u30b3\u30ed\u30ca\u30a6\u30a4\u30eb\u30b9\uff08\u65e5\u672c\u304b\u3089\u306e\u6e21\u822a\u8005\u30fb\u65e5\u672c\u4eba\u306b\u5bfe\u3059\u308b\u5404\u56fd\u30fb\u5730\u57df\u306e\u5165\u56fd\u5236\u9650\u63aa\u7f6e\u53ca\u3073\u5165\u56fd\u5f8c\u306e\u884c\u52d5\u5236\u9650\uff09|last=\u5916\u52d9\u7701|first=|date=|website=\u5916\u52d9\u7701 \u6d77\u5916\u5b89\u5168\u30db\u30fc\u30e0\u30da\u30fc\u30b8|language=ja|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref>\n* {{flag|Antigua and Barbuda}}: Visitors who have travelled through Austria, Belgium, Bulgaria, Canada, China (People's Rep.), Croatia, Cyprus, Czechia, Denmark, Estonia, Finland, France, Germany, Greece, Hungary, Iceland, Iran, Ireland (Rep.), Italy, Korea (Rep.), Latvia, Liechtenstein, Lithuania, Luxembourg, Malta, Netherlands, Norway, Poland, Portugal, Romania, Singapore, Slovakia, Slovenia, Spain, Sweden, Switzerland, USA or United Kingdom in the past 28 days are not allowed to enter or transit Antigua and Barbuda.<ref name=\"iatatravelcentre.com\"/> Foreigners from Japan (including flight crew) denied entry.<ref name=\":0\" />\n* {{flag|Armenia}}: Suspended visa-free travel for Chinese citizens.<ref name=\"20200131reutersA\"/> Visitors who have travelled through Austria, Belgium, China (People's Rep.), Denmark, France, Germany, Iran, Italy, Japan, Korea (Rep.), Netherlands, Norway, Spain, Sweden, Switzerland or United Kingdom in the past 14 days are not allowed to enter or transit Armenia.<ref name=\"iatatravelcentre.com\"/>\n* {{flag|Australia}}: Foreigners who have been in South Korea will not be allowed in until 14 days after leaving South Korea.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.abc.net.au/news/2020-03-05/coronavirus-travel-ban-korea-italy-china-iran/12027348|title=South Korea added to Australia's coronavirus travel ban list, restrictions for travellers from Italy|last=Worthington|first=political correspondent Brett|date=2020-03-05|website=ABC News|language=en-AU|access-date=2020-03-05}}</ref> Australian citizens must self-isolate for 14 days. Non-Australians who leave Iran must wait 14 days before entering Australia. Travellers are advised not to travel to Iran.<ref>{{cite web |author1=Australian Government Department of Health |title=Coronavirus (COVID-19) health alert |url=https://www.health.gov.au/news/health-alerts/novel-coronavirus-2019-ncov-health-alert |website=Australian Government Department of Health |accessdate=4 March 2020 |language=en |date=4 March 2020}}</ref>\n* {{flag|Bahrain}}: Visitors who have travelled through Austria, Belgium, China (People's Rep.), Czechia, Denmark, Estonia, Finland, France, Germany, Greece, Hungary, Iceland, Iran, Iraq, Korea (Rep.), Latvia, Liechtenstein, Lithuania, Luxembourg, Malta, Netherlands, Norway, Poland, Portugal, Slovakia, Slovenia, Spain, Sweden, Switzerland, United Kingdom and USA in the past 14 days are not allowed to enter or transit Bahrain.<ref name=\"iatatravelcentre.com\"/> Banned arrivals from Japan.<ref name=\":0\" />\n* {{flag|Barbados}}: Visitors from China's (People's Rep.), Europe, Iran, Korea (Rep.), United Kingdom or USA will be quarantined for 14 days.<ref name=\"iatatravelcentre.com\"/>\n* {{flag|Belize}}: Visitors who have travelled through European country, China (People's Rep.), Hong Kong (SAR China), Iran, Japan or Korea (Rep.) will be required to self-isolate.<ref name=\"iatatravelcentre.com\"/> Entry from Japan denied.<ref name=\":0\" />\n* {{flag|Bosnia and Herzegovina}}: Visitors from Austria, Belgium, China (People's Rep.) (Hubei - Wuhan Province), France, Germany, Iran, Italy, Japan, Korea (Rep.), Romania, Spain or Switzerland are not allowed to enter or transit Bosnia and Herzegovina.<ref name=\"iatatravelcentre.com\"/>\n* {{flag|Botswana}}: Visitors from Austria, Belgium, China (People's Rep.), Denmark, France, Germany, India, Iran, Italy, Japan, Korea (Rep.), Netherlands, Norway, Spain, Sweden, Switzerland, USA or United Kingdom are not allowed to enter or transit Botswana.<ref name=\"iatatravelcentre.com\"/>\n* {{flag|Bulgaria}}: Visitors from France, Germany, Italy, Netherlands, Spain, Switzerland can only transit through Bulgaria to return home, but are not allowed into the country.<ref name=\"iatatravelcentre.com\"/>\n* {{flag|Cambodia}}: Visitors from France, Germany, Iran, Italy, Spain or USA are not allowed to enter Cambodia.<ref name=\"iatatravelcentre.com\"/>\n* {{flag|China}}: Visitors who have travelled through Australia, Austria, Belgium, Canada, Czechia, Denmark, Finland, France, Germany, Greece, Iran, Italy, Korea (Rep.), Malaysia, Netherlands, Norway, Qatar, Saudi Arabia, Spain, Sweden, Switzerland, United Kingdom or USA in the past 14 days will be quarantined for 14 days.<ref name=\"iatatravelcentre.com\"/>\n* {{flag|Fiji}}: Visitors from China (People's Rep.), Europe, Iran, Korea (Rep.) or USA are not allowed to enter or transit Fiji.<ref name=\"iatatravelcentre.com\"/>\n* {{flag|Gabon}}: Visitors who have travelled through Austria, Belgium, Bulgaria, China (People's Rep.), Croatia, Cyprus, Czechia, Denmark, Estonia, Finland, France, Germany, Greece, Hungary, Italy, Ireland (Rep.), Japan, Korea (Rep.), Latvia, Liechtenstein, Lithuania, Luxembourg, Malta, Netherlands, Norway, Poland, Portugal, Romania, Spain, Slovakia, Slovenia, Sweden, Switzerland, USA or the United Kingdom in the past 14 days are not allowed to enter or transit Gabon.<ref name=\"iatatravelcentre.com\"/><ref name=\":0\" />\n*{{flag|Germany}}: Effective March 16, 2020 Germany has partially closed its borders with France, Austria, Denmark, Luxembourg, and Switzerland. However, goods will continue to flow between the countries to curb panic-buying.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-51897069|title=Germany to impose border controls over coronavirus|date=March 15, 2020|via=BBC News}}</ref>\n* {{flag|Grenada}}: Visitors who have travelled through Austria, Belgium, Bulgaria, China (People's Rep.), Croatia, Cyprus, Czechia, Denmark, Estonia, Finland, France, Germany, Greece, Hungary, Iceland, Iran, Ireland (Rep.), Italy, Korea (Rep.), Latvia, Liechtenstein, Lithuania, Luxembourg, Malta, Netherlands, Norway, Poland, Portugal, Romania, Slovakia, Slovenia, Spain, Sweden, Switzerland, USA or the United Kingdom in the past 14 days are not allowed to enter Grenada.<ref name=\"iatatravelcentre.com\"/> Arrivals from Japan denied.<ref name=\":0\" />\n* {{flag|Guatemala}}: Banned arrivals from Canada and the United States starting mid-March.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-guatemala-idUSKBN211010|title=Guatemala bans arrivals from U.S., Canada to fight coronavirus|date=March 14, 2020|via=www.reuters.com}}</ref> Japanese nationals (except diplomats and those with residency permits) banned from entry.<ref name=\":0\" />\n* {{flag|Haiti}}: Visitors who have travelled through China (People's Rep.), France, Germany, Iran, Italy or Korea (Rep.) in the past 14 days are not allowed to enter or transit Haiti.<ref name=\"iatatravelcentre.com\"/> Visitors from Japan denied entry.<ref name=\":0\" />\n* {{flag|Hong Kong}}: Arrivals from the Schengen zone must be quarantined for 14 days starting from March 17.<ref>[https://www.scmp.com/news/hong-kong/health-environment/article/3075025/hong-kong-toddler-tests-positive-coronavirus Coronavirus: Hong Kong imposes quarantine restrictions on 26 European countries in Schengen zone] 13 March 2020, ''www.scmp.com'', accessed 15 March 2020</ref> Arrivals from Japan denied entry.<ref name=\":0\" />\n*{{flag|India}}: Issued a travel advisory on February 2, 2020 warning all people residing in India to not travel to China, suspended E-visas from China and stated that anyone who has travelled to China since 15 January (to an indefinite point in the future) could be quarantined.<ref name=\"twitter1224015130\"/> Has suspended all regular and e-visas issued on, or before, March 3, 2020 and banned travellers from South Korea from entering India through all ports of entry. People who need to travel to India, due to compelling reasons, need to apply for a fresh visa.<ref name=\"India Advisory\">{{cite web |title=Advisory: Travel and Visa restrictions related to COVID-19 |url=https://boi.gov.in/content/advisory-travel-and-visa-restrictions-related-covid-19 |website=Bureau of Immigration |publisher=Ministry of Home Affairs, Government of India |language=en}}</ref> Flights from Japan and e-visa issuance to Japanese nationals suspended.<ref name=\":0\" /> \n*{{flag|Indonesia}}: Announced on February 3, 2020 that it would ban passenger flights and sea freight from and to China starting on February 5 and until further notice. Live animal imports and other products were banned as well.<ref name=\"detik4884030\"/><ref name=\"AutoDW-166\"/><ref name=\"AutoDW-167\"/> An entry ban applies to visitors who travelled to [[Daegu]] and [[North Gyeongsang Province|Gyeongsangbuk]] within the past 14 days.<ref name=\"20200305indonesia\">{{cite news|url=https://www.straitstimes.com/asia/se-asia/coronavirus-indonesia-bans-entry-and-transit-of-foreigners-from-worst-stricken-regions|title=Coronavirus: Indonesia bans entry and transit of foreigners from worst-stricken regions in Iran, Italy and South Korea|date=5 March 2020|work=The Straits Times|accessdate=8 March 2020|language=en}}</ref> Visitors who have traveled from France, Germany, Iran, Italy, Spain, Switzerland, United Kingdom or Vatican City (Holy See) are not allowed to enter or transit Indonesia.<ref name=\":7\">{{cite web|url=https://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2020/03/17/covid-19-indonesia-suspends-visa-free-policy-expands-ban-for-people-from-worst-hit-countries.html|title=COVID-19: Indonesia suspends visa-free policy, expands ban for people from worst-hit countries|last=Post|first=The Jakarta|website=The Jakarta Post|language=en|access-date=2020-03-18}}</ref> Visitors from Japan not allowed entry.<ref name=\":0\" />\n* {{flag|Iraq}}: The government announced [[Basra International Airport]] would deny entry to passengers coming from China.<ref name=\"20200131reutersB\"/> Flights from Japan denied entry.<ref name=\":0\" />\n* {{flag|Israel}}: Initially banned citizens or visitors of [[Germany]], [[France]], [[Spain]], [[Switzerland]], [[Austria]], [[Andorra]] and [[San Marino]] unless they have proof that they have a place to self-quarantine for 14 days on March 6.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.timesofisrael.com/israel-begins-restrictions-on-visitors-from-5-european-nations-over-virus-fears/|title=Israel begins restrictions on visitors from 5 European nations over virus fears|date=2020-03-06|last=|first=|website=Times of Israel|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-03-07}}</ref> Entry ban from Japan and South Korea since February 23.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.japantimes.co.jp/news/2020/02/23/national/science-health/israel-south-korea-japan-flight-covid19/|title=Israel bans foreign visitors who traveled to Japan or South Korea as coronavirus fears surge|date=2020-02-23|work=The Japan Times Online|access-date=2020-04-02|language=en-US|issn=0447-5763}}</ref> On March 9, Israel instituted a blanket 14-day quarantine on all visitors and returning citizens.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.haaretz.com/israel-news/.premium-israeli-with-coronavirus-in-severe-condition-israel-may-quarantine-some-u-s-arrivals-1.8638322|title=Israel Extends Coronavirus Quarantine Orders to All Arrivals, 42 Cases Confirmed |date=2020-03-09|last=|first=|website=Haaretz|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-03-09}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Italy}}: Has suspended all passenger air traffic to Italy from mainland China, Hong Kong, Macau and Taiwan. The [[Italian Civil Aviation Authority]] [[NOTAM]] says that effective January 31, all passenger flights from China, including the [[special administrative regions of China|special administrative regions]] of Hong Kong and [[Macau]], as well as Taiwan, are suspended until further notice, on request of the Italian health authorities. Aircraft that were flying to Italy when the NOTAM was published were cleared to land.<ref name=\"Italy flights\"/><ref name=\"20200131enac\"/> Despite direct flights ban from/to China, Hong Kong, Macau and Taiwan, Chinese citizens with a Schengen Visa issued by another Schengen Country were allowed to enter Italy via flights with a stopover in other countries.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.corriere.it/cronache/20_gennaio_30/coronavirus-l-italia-ferma-voli-la-cina-ma-5-aerei-stanno-arrivando-roma-milano-4c159766-43a8-11ea-bdc8-faf1f56f19b7.shtml|title=Coronavirus, l'Italia ferma i voli con la Cina, gli ultimi aerei sono arrivati a Roma e Milano|language=it|date=30 January 2020|work= Corriere della Sera|first= Leonardo|last= Berbieri|access-date=March 25, 2020|trans-title=Italy stops flight from/to China, last flight have just landed at Rome and Milan airports}}</ref>\n* {{flag|Jamaica}}: Visitors who have travelled through China (People's Rep.), Chinese Taipei, France, Germany, Hong Kong (SAR China), Iran, Italy, Korea (Rep.), Macao (SAR China), Singapore, Spain or United Kingdom in the past 14 days are not allowed to enter or transit Jamaica.<ref name=\"iatatravelcentre.com\"/> Banned arrivals from Japan.<ref name=\":0\" />\n*{{flag|Japan}}: At the beginning of March, Japan revoked existing visas of people coming from China.<ref name=\":4\">{{cite web|url=https://www3.nhk.or.jp/nhkworld/en/news/20200306_23/|title=Japan's Cabinet approves visa cancellation policy {{!}} NHK WORLD-JAPAN News|website=NHK WORLD|language=en|access-date=2020-03-06}}</ref> From 3 April, foreign travellers present in the past 14 days in Europe (excluding Belarus, Russia and Ukraine) and select countries of Asia (Brunei, China, Hong Kong, Indonesia, Macau, Malaysia, Philippines, Republic of Korea, Singapore, Taiwan, Thailand, Vietnam), Oceania (Australia, New Zealand), North America (Canada, United States), Latin America (Bolivia, Brazil, Chile, Dominica, Ecuador, Panama), the Middle East (Bahrain, Iran, Israel, Turkey), and Africa (C\u00f4te d'Ivoire, Democratic Republic of the Congo, Egypt, Mauritius, Morocco) are barred from entry. Japanese citizens returning from those countries are required to undergo testing and potential quarantine.<ref>{{cite web |title=Coronavirus (COVID-19) advisory information {{!}} Travel Japan {{!}} JNTO |url=https://www.japan.travel/en/coronavirus/ |website=Japan National Tourism Organization (JNTO) |accessdate=7 April 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Kazakhstan}}: Suspended 72-hour visa-free transit for Chinese passengers.<ref name=\"AutoDW-156\"/> Arrivals from Japan banned.<ref name=\":0\" />\n*{{flag|Kiribati}}: Travellers who have been to a country with reported cases in the past 14 days prohibited from entering except with a medical certificate.<ref>{{cite news |title=UK travel advice: What countries have travel bans amid coronavirus outbreak? |url=https://metro.co.uk/2020/03/12/uk-travel-advice-countries-travel-bans-coronavirus-outbreak-12385713/ |accessdate=1 April 2020 |work=Metro |date=12 March 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Kuwait}}:<ref name=\"aa1719723\"/> Transport and visas [https://kuwaitvisa.com/travel-restrictions/ have been suspended between Kuwait and a number of countries], with nationals of certain sovereign states being temporarily banned from entering. Any traveler who has visited affected regions face similar restrictions.\n* {{flag|Macau}}: Entry denied to all travellers except residents of mainland China, Hong Kong, Macau, or Taiwan.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://macaunews.mo/macau-prohibits-non-residents-from-entering-macau-with-the-exception-of-those-from-mainland-china-hong-kong-and-taiwan/|title=Macau Prohibits Non-Residents from Entering Macau with the exception of those from Mainland China, Hong Kong and Taiwan|website=Macau News |accessdate=19 March 2020}}</ref> Previously, restrictions were implemented for travellers coming from a smaller set of countries.\n* {{flag|Maldives}}: Visitors who have travelled through Bangladesh, China (People's Rep.), Iran, Italy, Malaysia, Spain, Sri Lanka, United Kingdom or in North Gyeongsang and South Gyeongsang Provinces in Korea (Rep.), Ile-de-France and Grand Est (regions of France) and Bavaria, North Rhine Westphalia and Baden-Wuerttemberg (regions of Germany) in the past 14 days are not allowed to enter or transit Maldives.<ref name=\"iatatravelcentre.com\"/> Suspended visa issuance Japanese nationals, and banned tourist-related entries.<ref name=\":0\" />\n*{{flag|Micronesia}} has introduced a strict travel ban, banning anyone who had been in China anytime since January 2020 \u2014 or had been in any other affected country in the last 14 days \u2014 from entering Micronesia.<ref name=\"slate FSM\">{{cite web|url=https://slate.com/technology/2020/03/micronesia-drastic-coronavirus-travel-ban.html|title=The Most Drastic Anti-Coronavirus Travel Ban in the World|first=Rachel|last=Withers|date=March 5, 2020|website=Slate Magazine}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Nauru}}: Prohibited passengers who have been to Hong Kong, Iran, Italy, Japan, Macau, mainland China, or South Korea in the past 21 days.<ref name=\"iatatravelcentre.com\"/><ref name=\":0\" />\n*{{flag|New Zealand}}: Announced that it will deny entry to all travellers from China and that it will order its citizens to self-isolate for 14 days if they are returning from China.<ref name=\"WP\"/>\n* {{flag|Samoa}}: Visitors who have travelled through Australia, Austria, Bahrain, Belgium, Canada, China (People's Rep.), Chinese Taipei, Czechia, Denmark, France, Germany, Greece, Hong Kong (SAR China), Iceland, Italy, Iran, Japan, Korea (Rep.), Kuwait, Luxembourg, Macao (SAR China), Malaysia, Netherlands, Norway, Qatar, Singapore, Spain, Sweden, Switzerland, Thailand, United Arab Emirates or USA are not allowed to enter or transit Samoa.<ref name=\"iatatravelcentre.com\"/> Controversially, Samoa denied entry to several Samoan citizens, which was criticized as a violation of international law.<ref name=\"AutoDW-159\"/><ref name=\"AutoDW-160\"/>\n* {{flag|Singapore}}: Visitors who are from Germany, France, Spain and Italy are not allowed to enter or transit Singapore, and from March 16, 2020 at 11.59pm, it will be extended to all ASEAN countries, United Kingdom and Switzerland. Citizens must be quarantined for 14 days.<ref name=\"20200303mohsg\" /><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/singapore-residents-advised-to-defer-all-non-essential-travel-for-next-30-days-as-part-of|title=Singaporeans advised to defer all non-essential travel for next 30 days, as part of new Covid-19 measures|date=March 15, 2020|website=The Straits Times}}</ref> Entries from Japan (including transits) not allowed, except for those with permanent residence permits.<ref name=\":0\" />\n*{{flag|Somalia}}: banned passengers who had been to China, Iran, South Korea, or Italy in the past 14 days.<ref name=\"Somalia bans entry\">{{cite news |title=COVID-19: Somalia bans entry from worst-hit countries |url=https://www.aa.com.tr/en/latest-on-coronavirus-outbreak/covid-19-somalia-bans-entry-from-worst-hit-countries/1766837 |accessdate=22 March 2020 |work=www.aa.com.tr}}</ref> Banned flights from Japan.<ref name=\":0\" />\n* {{flag|South Africa}}: Visitors from China (People's Rep.), France, Germany, Iran, Italy, Japan, Korea (Rep.), Spain, Switzerland, USA or United Kingdom are not allowed to enter or transit South Africa.<ref name=\"iatatravelcentre.com\"/><ref name=\":0\" />\n*{{flag|Taiwan}}: Prohibited entry to Chinese nationals and foreign nationals who have travelled to mainland China, Hong Kong, or Macau in the past 14 days.<ref name=\"TWCDC06Feb2020\"/> Entry from Japan denied.<ref name=\":0\" />\n*{{flag|Trinidad and Tobago}}: Health Minister [[Ter\u00adrance Deyals\u00adingh]] announced that [[Trinidad and Tobago]] had decided to implement restrictions on persons traveling from [[China]]. Persons who are living or who have visited China, will be barred from entering Trinidad and Tobago unless they had already been out of China 14 days prior to attempting to travel to Trinidad & Tobago.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.looptt.com/content/covid-19-tt-closes-borders-non-nationals-14-days |title = COVID-19: T&T closes borders to non-nationals for 14 days}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.caribbean360.com/news/trinidad-tobago-shuts-out-international-community-for-two-weeks-to-stem-spread-of-covid-19 |title = Trinidad & Tobago Shuts Out International Community to Stem Spread of COVID-19; Schools Closed|date = 16 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"TT Cabinet announces 14-day travel restrictions\">{{cite web |url=http://www.guardian.co.tt/neo/NeoProxy.dll?app=NeoDirect&com=6/2/1042978/7a4c342a7f |title=Cabinet announces 14-day travel restrictions from China |website=guardian.co.tt |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200222113407/https://www.guardian.co.tt/neo/NeoProxy.dll?app=NeoDirect&com=6%2F2%2F1042978%2F7a4c342a7f |archive-date=22 February 2020 |access-date=27 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.guardian.co.tt/news/3-more-european-nations-on-tts-covidrestricted-list-6.2.1076451.75af2508a7 | title=3 more European nations on T&T's COVID-restricted list}}</ref> Travellers whose flights originate from&nbsp;Italy, South Korea, Singapore, Japan, Iran, Germany, Spain, and France are also to be restricted.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.guardian.co.tt/news/3-more-european-nations-on-tts-covidrestricted-list-6.2.1076451.75af2508a7 |title = 3 more European nations on T&T's COVID-restricted list}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Turkey}}: announced it would suspend all flights from China till the end of February and begin scanning passengers coming from Japan, Taiwan, Hong Kong, Singapore, South Korea, and Malaysia at airports.<ref name=\"gazeteduvar\"/><ref name=\"aa1722860\"/> All Iranian nationals are banned from entering Turkey. Passengers who have transited through or have been in Iran in the past 14 days are not allowed to transit or enter Turkey. Also suspended the incoming flights from Iran on February 23, 2020,<ref name=\"Hurriyet\">{{cite news |title=9 Avrupa \u00fclkesine u\u00e7u\u015f yasa\u011f\u0131 |url=https://www.hurriyet.com.tr/gundem/son-dakika-haberi-9-avrupa-ulkesine-ucus-yasagi-41468591 |accessdate=13 March 2020 |work=H\u00fcrriyet |date=13 March 2020 |language=tr}}</ref> Nationals of Austria, Belgium, Denmark, France, Germany, the Netherlands, Norway, Spain and Sweden are not allowed to enter Turkey. Passengers who have transited through or have been in Austria, Belgium, Denmark, France, Germany, the Netherlands, Norway, Spain and Sweden in the past 14 days are not allowed to transit or enter Turkey. Also suspended the incoming flights from these countries effective from March 14, 2020. This restriction does not apply to nationals of Turkey and residents of Turkey.<ref name=\"iatatravelcentre.com\"/> Tourists arriving from these locations will not be allowed to pass through national immigration even if they have a valid eVisa or another form of travel authorization. Foreign visitors who have been in these nations up to [https://www.visasturkey.com/travel-and-entry-restrictions/ 14 days prior to arriving in Turkey] will also face restrictions and barriers to entry. Flights from Japan not allowed entry.<ref name=\":0\" />\n*{{flag|United States}}: On January 31, 2020, the United States declared the virus a [[Public health emergency (United States)|public health emergency]]. Starting February 2, all inbound passengers who have been to Hubei in the previous 14 days will be put under quarantine for up to 14 days. American citizens who have travelled to the rest of mainland China will be allowed to continue their travel home if they are asymptomatic, but will be monitored by local health departments.<ref name=\"nbcnews1127856\"/> As of March 2, foreign nationals who have travelled to Iran within the past 14 days are denied permission to enter the US.<ref name=\"2020-03-02cnn\"/> American citizens and permanent residents returning to the United States who have travelled to Iran within the previous 14 days must enter through an approved airport.<ref name=\"2020-03-02cnn\"/><ref name=\"iatatravelcentre.com\"/> Suspended incoming travel from the [[Schengen area]] in Europe, beginning at 23:59 [[Eastern Time Zone|ET]] on March 13.<ref name=EUban>{{cite web|url=https://www.whitehouse.gov/presidential-actions/proclamation-suspension-entry-immigrants-nonimmigrants-certain-additional-persons-pose-risk-transmitting-2019-novel-coronavirus/|title=Proclamation\u2014Suspension of Entry as Immigrants and Nonimmigrants of Certain Additional Persons Who Pose a Risk of Transmitting 2019 Novel Coronavirus|date=2020-03-11|website=The White House|first=Donald|last=Trump}}</ref> The official proclamation states that this restriction applies only to foreign nationals traveling to the United States, if they have been to a country within the [[Schengen area]] in the past 14 days. The ban does not apply to for example legal permanent residents and most immediate family members of U.S. citizens.<ref name=EUban/> Also, cargo and trading goods are not affected.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dw.com/en/coronavirus-latest-trump-suspends-travel-from-europes-schengen-countries/a-52731894|title=Coronavirus latest: Trump suspends travel from Europe's Schengen countries|website=Deutsche Welle|language=en-GB|access-date=2020-03-12}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-51846923|title=Trump halts travel from Europe to US|date=2020-03-12|work=BBC News|access-date=2020-03-12|language=en-GB}}</ref> On March 14, Trump administration extended the ban to include United Kingdom and Ireland.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.foxnews.com/politics/trump-european-travel-ban-uk-ireland|title=Trump administration to extend European travel ban to include UK and Ireland|last=Shaw|first=Adam|date=2020-03-14|website=Fox News|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-14}}</ref> The restrictions will reportedly be in place for 30 days,<ref>{{Cite news|last=Specia|first=Megan|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/03/12/world/europe/trump-travel-ban-coronavirus.html|title=What You Need to Know About Trump's European Travel Ban|date=2020-03-12|work=The New York Times|access-date=2020-03-15|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref> however the official proclamation does not contain that time limit, stating; \"This proclamation shall remain in effect until terminated by the President.\"<ref name=\"EUban\" />\n* {{flag|Uruguay}}: Visitors from Argentina, China (People's Rep.), France, Germany, Iran, Italy, Japan, Korea (Rep.), Singapore or Spain are not allowed to enter or transit Uruguay.<ref name=\"iatatravelcentre.com\"/>\n* {{flag|Vietnam}}: Suspended visa issuance for Chinese tourists.<ref name=\"20200130reuters\"/> Suspended the visa waiver for citizens of Denmark, Finland, France, Germany, Norway, Spain, Sweden and United Kingdom effective from March 12, 2020,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mofa.gov.vn/en/nr040807104143/nr040807105001/ns200311161021|title=Temporary suspension of unilateral visa waiver to European countries regarding the COVID-19 situation|publisher=[[Ministry of Foreign Affairs (Vietnam)|Vietnam MFA]]}}</ref> and for Italy from March 3.<ref name=\"vietnam-mfa-updates\">{{cite web|url=http://www.mofa.gov.vn/en/tt_baochi/pbnfn/ns200312141207|title=Updated information on COVID-19 pandemic|publisher=[[Ministry of Foreign Affairs (Vietnam)|Vietnam MFA]]}}</ref> Entry from Japan denied.<ref name=\":0\" /> Embassies and travel agencies have also been instructed not to issue regular visas to citizens from the above countries, for the time being.  Vietnam has announced that from 12:00 (UTC+07:00) on March 15, 2020 all foreign nationals will be refused entry to Vietnam if in the previous 14 days they have been to the UK, or any Schengen country, even in transit. This restriction will be in place for 30 days.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gov.uk/foreign-travel-advice/vietnam?utm_source=c37d8398-0338-4191-a8d3-82f8a146a447&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=govuk-notifications&utm_content=immediate|title=Vietnam: Foreign travel advice|website=Gov.uk|accessdate=March 15, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mofa.gov.vn/en/nr040807104143/nr040807105001/ns200314083802|title=Temporary regulatory change on entry, exit for foreigners|publisher=[[Ministry of Foreign Affairs (Vietnam)|Vietnam MFA]]}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n{{Div col}}\n*[[Impact of the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic on aviation]]\n*[[Impact of the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic on cinema]]\n*[[2020 coronavirus pandemic on cruise ships]]\n*[[Impact of the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic on education]]\n*[[Impact of the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic on religion]]\n*[[Impact of the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic on politics]]\n*[[Impact of the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic on sports]]\n*[[Impact of the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic on television]]\n{{End div col}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist\n| colwidth = 30em\n| refs =\n\n<ref name=\"20200131reutersA\">{{cite news |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/china-health-armenia-idUSR4N29R01Z |title=Armenia suspends visa-free travel for Chinese citizens over virus fears -deputy PM |date=31 January 2020 |agency=Reuters |access-date=10 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200131224329/https://www.reuters.com/article/china-health-armenia-idUSR4N29R01Z |archive-date=31 January 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"20200131reutersB\">{{cite news |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-iraq-idUSKBN1ZU2U5 |title=Iraq's Basra airport to deny entry to travellers from China and Chinese citizens over coronavirus \u2013 state news agency |date=31 January 2020 |agency=Reuters |access-date=10 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200203170236/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-iraq-idUSKBN1ZU2U5 |archive-date=3 February 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"AutoDW-156\">{{cite web |url=https://en.trend.az/casia/kazakhstan/3182640.html |title=Kazakh prime minister orders to suspend visa-free entry for Chinese transit passengers |date=26 January 2020 |website=Trend.Az |access-date=10 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200127141522/https://en.trend.az/casia/kazakhstan/3182640.html |archive-date=27 January 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"aa1719723\">{{cite web |url=https://www.aa.com.tr/en/asia-pacific/kuwait-suspends-china-hong-kong-flights/1719723 |title=Kuwait suspends China, Hong Kong flights |website=aa.com.tr |access-date=10 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200201175758